column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4150_LongDesc", "In the Western kingdoms of Aquilonia and Nemedia, the practise of using wooden signs to provide warning and information for travellers and merchants has been established for centuries.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4168_LongDesc", "In the Western kingdoms of Aquilonia and Nemedia, the practise of using wooden signs to provide warning and information for travellers and merchants has been established for centuries.\nOnce a signpost is placed, it can be used to write a custom message for any travellers to read.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4176_ShortDesc", "A decorative egg")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4176_LongDesc", "An imitation of a serpentman egg made out of corrupted stone and infused with a fragment of power.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4177_ShortDesc", "A throne made of corrupted stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4177_LongDesc", "Unlike other chairs, a throne gives the one who sits in it authority above and beyond that of an ordinary man.\nBattles have always been fought for this kind of power, and they always will be.\nSitting on a throne of any kind will increase confidence and prowess for a period.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4220_ShortDesc", "A die shaped from bones")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4220_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Conan strode through a garden, where great pale blossoms nodded in the starlight, and entered the taproom, where a Stygian with the shaven head of a student sat at a table brooding over nameless mysteries, and some nondescripts wrangled over a game of dice in a corner.</> - Shadows in Zamboula\n\nA favored pass-time by many adventurers is playing dice. With taverns being few and far apart in the Exiled lands, one has to make do with what one can.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4230_ShortDesc", "A framed painting")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4230_LongDesc", "Talented artists are few and far between but the fact that even in the Exiled Lands, art such as this survives and thrives is comforting. Amongst all the bloodshed one can still appreciate the talent of the painter.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10001_ShortDesc", "Roughly hewn chunk of stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10001_LongDesc", "Most humble of materials and most common, stone is the building block of civilization. From the primitive weapons of Picts to the marble sheathed palaces of Aquilonian Kings, stone is the foundation upon which all is predicated.\nEven the elder races, who vanished from the earth without a trace, left behind great ruined cities of brooding stone to mark their passing.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10002_ShortDesc", "A queen bee used for producing honey")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10002_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Our wisdom flows so sweet. Taste and see.</> - The Buzzing\nBeehives pulse with activity and life - and at the beating heart of the hive is the queen bee. Usually the mother of all the bees in the hive - without her the hive would no longer produce honey.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10003_ShortDesc", "A worker bee")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10003_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Our wisdom flows so sweet. Taste and see.</> - The Buzzing\nThey give their lives to the hive, and the hive gives honey to those who take it. This is perhaps, a metaphor for kingdoms and those who plunder them.\nOr simply the lives of bees.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10005_ShortDesc", "Strip of bark torn from a tree")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10005_LongDesc", "Strip of bark torn from a tree. Use for tanning leather and as a meagre fuel source. A byproduct of using bark in the tanning process is Tar.
The leatherworkers of Kordava are renowned for their supple and pliant leather. Their process for tanning, and the bark that they use, is a well-guarded secret.
Teas brewed from the bark of certain trees are rumoured to cure many different kinds of ailment.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10010_ShortDesc", "Bones infused by foul Darfari alchemy")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10010_LongDesc", "These bones can be infused with life using Darfari black arts. The result is often unstable but the use of a Fragment of Power reduces this risk.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10011_ShortDesc", "A log hewn from a tree")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10011_LongDesc", "Wood is an abundant source of fuel and building material.\nReadily available and easily shaped with the right tools, wood is ubiquitous in the weapons and buildings of primitive tribes and mighty nations.  \nWood allows for the creation of fire and its easy transport.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10012_ShortDesc", "A sturdy branch fallen from a tree")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10012_LongDesc", "Branches can be used to create rudimentary weapons and tools, which can then be used to shape wood for more beneficial purposes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10020_ShortDesc", "A steel bar infused with a strange essence")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10020_LongDesc", "This steel bar is extremely malleable and tough. Steel such as this was once used to fashion the weapons wielded by, and the armor worn by, the Khari.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10021_ShortDesc", "Bones and bone fragments from animals and humans")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10021_LongDesc", "Used by shamans and witch doctors for rituals and ceremonial gear, bone is a staple of crafting primitive equipment. 
The people of Darfar are known for ritual cannibalism as a part of their worship of Yog. They use the remains of their victims to craft horrifying weapons and armours.
Bone is not particularly durable and will shatter easily upon iron or steel.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10022_ShortDesc", "Bones taken from a dragon raised to life through terrible ritual")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10022_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails

Through the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.

The sad reality of dragons was that they could not fly, they did not breathe fire or acid, and they were not particularly intelligent. They were simply gigantic predators that lived centuries ago.

Through their arts, the Giant-kings resurrected dragons from the bones that they could find. They kept them as pets and bred them for battle in their gladiatorial games. 

Their bones are particularly strong and can be worked into powerful weapons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10023_ShortDesc", "Horn taken from a dragon raised to life through terrible ritual")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10023_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails

Through the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.

The sad reality of dragons was that they could not fly, they did not breathe fire or acid, and they were not particularly intelligent. They were simply gigantic predators that lived centuries ago.

Through their arts, the Giant-kings resurrected dragons from the bones that they could find. They kept them as pets and bred them for battle in their gladiatorial games. 

Their horns are particularly strong and can be worked into powerful weapons.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10024_ShortDesc", "An ice-shard blessed by Ymir")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10024_LongDesc", "The ice shard is cold as death to the touch and seems to writhe in your hands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11001_ShortDesc", "Greyish chunk of stone that can be smelted to obtain iron")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11001_LongDesc", "Run through with metallic veins, this ore can be treated in a furnace to create Iron bars.\nIronstone can be strengthened with additional catalysts during the smelting process. Alchemists guard the secrets of their catalysts jealously, so experimentation with a cauldron is required.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11011_ShortDesc", "The glowing heart of the forge")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11011_LongDesc", "Coal is a versatile, long lasting fuel. Serious smithing requires a supply of coal to reach the high temperatures for smelting workable metals.
Coal is required for the process of transforming iron into the steel.
Harlots and nobles often use charcoal to whiten their teeth and healers often keep a small supply handy as a simple remedy for stomach ailments.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11012_ShortDesc", "This tablet contains the knowledge of the ancients")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11012_LongDesc", "Combining the fragments into this completed piece has revealed secrets beyond the ages. Reading this tablet will grant you additional feat points, even beyond studying the individual fragments.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11013_ShortDesc", "This blend of unholy substances smell of rot and death")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11013_LongDesc", "Distilled rot from a variety of disgusting ingredients, this essence will in short time turn any raw meat into rotten meat when cooked. The Essence does not seem to be reduced by doing this, and while it will evaporate over time naturally, using it to cause meat to rot does not consume it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11016_ShortDesc", "A key")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11016_LongDesc", "This opens the door leading to the inner sanctum of the Warmaker.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11017_ShortDesc", "This is a fragment of a key")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11017_LongDesc", "When combined, these fragments will make a key.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11018_ShortDesc", "A key")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11018_LongDesc", "This opens the door leading to the arena of the Warmaker.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11019_ShortDesc", "A key")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11019_LongDesc", "This key opens the door to the dungeons of the Warmaker\'s Sanctuary.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11020_ShortDesc", "A bronze coin")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11020_LongDesc", "This coin is made of bronze. \nThese coins are of dubious mercantile value but can probably be melted down to obtain base metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11021_ShortDesc", "Thick viscous fluid")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11021_LongDesc", "This blood is black as night and smells faintly of sulphur.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11022_ShortDesc", "A shimmering crystal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11022_LongDesc", "Brittle, impossible to work with conventional tools, crystal is mostly used for focusing light and creating rudimentary lenses.\nThe Black Seers of Mount Yimsha craft great lenses to aid in their astrological divinations. Black sorceries gain potency when the heavens are in certain configurations.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11023_ShortDesc", "A shimmering crystal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11023_LongDesc", "Brittle, impossible to work with conventional tools, crystal is mostly used for focusing light and creating rudimentary lenses.\nThe Black Seers of Mount Yimsha craft great lenses to aid in their astrological divinations. Black sorceries gain potency when the heavens are in certain configurations.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11024_ShortDesc", "A shimmering crystal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11024_LongDesc", "Brittle, impossible to work with conventional tools, crystal is mostly used for focusing light and creating rudimentary lenses.\nThe Black Seers of Mount Yimsha craft great lenses to aid in their astrological divinations. Black sorceries gain potency when the heavens are in certain configurations.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11025_ShortDesc", "A rare spice")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11025_LongDesc", "These spices are the types of spices that burn twice.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11026_ShortDesc", "Torn scraps of cloth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11026_LongDesc", "These scraps once belonged to some form of clothing.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11027_ShortDesc", "A tablet inscribed with symbols")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11027_LongDesc", "These symbols are night-impossible to understand, yet it seems like their mere presence claws at your mind when you look at them - as if the words themselves wishes to be read.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11028_ShortDesc", "A feather")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11028_LongDesc", "Used primarily in the creation of arrows and for stuffing cushions, feathers come in all sizes and colors. Soft, downy feathers plucked from the breast of an animal are the best for cushioning, while stiffer feather taken from the tail of a bird are more useful for keeping arrows true in the air.\n\nThese feathers are taken from the wild birds that roam the Exiled Lands - so ferocious, but oh so delicious as well.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11029_ShortDesc", "A feather")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11029_LongDesc", "Used primarily in the creation of arrows and for stuffing cushions, feathers come in all sizes and colors. Soft, downy feathers plucked from the breast of an animal are the best for cushioning, while stiffer feather taken from the tail of a bird are more useful for keeping arrows true in the air.\n\nThese feathers are taken from the wild birds that roam the Exiled Lands - so ferocious, but oh so delicious as well.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11030_ShortDesc", "Shards of Obsidian")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11030_LongDesc", "A shard of obsidian - much sharper and stronger than normal glass.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11031_ShortDesc", "A lump of Obsidian shaped like a gemstone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11031_LongDesc", "Sometimes, although rarely,  the heat of the Volcano melts the Obsidian into lumps like these.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11032_ShortDesc", "For carrying stuff")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11032_LongDesc", "Also for carrying things.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11033_ShortDesc", "This gemstone has lost its power")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11033_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'They are jewels, fused with radium. You rub them with your thumb to make them glow, and rub them again, the opposite way, to extinguish them.\'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk\n\nThe product of a science long vanished in the ancient past, these gems seem to glow indefinitely when activated. There is a cost, however, as those who use the Radium Gems seem to slowly lose their grip on sanity, whispering to themselves of green stoned cities and the nameless horrors that stalk them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11034_ShortDesc", "Scales from a beast")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11034_LongDesc", "These scales are incredibly tough and their edges are as sharp as knives.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11035_ShortDesc", "A flower collected from the Volcano")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11035_LongDesc", "These flowers only grow in the most volcanic and ashes parts of the Exiled Lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11036_ShortDesc", "A key")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11036_LongDesc", "This opens a lock somewhere. Unless the rust gets to it first.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11037_ShortDesc", "A key")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11044_ShortDesc", "A leather journal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11044_LongDesc", "For most, journals are used for writing things in. For Cimmerians, they are used as kindling for the fire.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11045_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">I have known many gods. He who denies them is as blind as he who trusts them too deeply.</> - The Queen of the Black Coast")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11051_ShortDesc", "Transparent, shimmering stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11051_LongDesc", "Brittle, impossible to work with conventional tools, crystal is mostly used for focusing light and creating rudimentary lenses.\nThe Black Seers of Mount Yimsha craft great lenses to aid in their astrological divinations. Black sorceries gain potency when the heavens are in certain configurations.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11052_ShortDesc", "A chunk of ore flecked with silver fragments")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11052_LongDesc", "Too weak to create effective weapons, silver is primarily for currency, ornamentation and the backing of polished mirrors. 

Silver can be effective against demonic creatures and spirits. Many a mercenary always keeps a single silver coin with them to ward off curses and dark creatures.

This chunk of ore can be smelted and used to forge weapons, but any such weapon will break after anything more than a single hit.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11053_ShortDesc", "A chunk of ore flecked with golden fragments")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11053_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">On the brink, under his very hand as he crouched, he found it, a thin vein of sparkling gold running from an outcropping of ore to the edge and down across the silvery floor.</> - People of the Black Circle

Merchants and Kings alike will tell you that gold is more powerful than any sorcery. It is gold that keeps bellies full, armies equipped, and the commoners entertained. A pauper may be free, but gold offers an entirely different type of freedom.

Gold is too soft to be used in the forging of weapons, but it is a highly sought after alchemical ingredient. It can be ground into a fine dust and ingested or melted down and used to create jewelry and other trinkets.

Some sages argue that gold has properties that ward against creatures of the Outer Dark, but other, wiser sages have pointed out that wearing gold to ward off such creatures will attract the attention of a complete different class of unsavory being.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11054_ShortDesc", "An ingot of mostly pure gold")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11054_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">On the brink, under his very hand as he crouched, he found it, a thin vein of sparkling gold running from an outcropping of ore to the edge and down across the silvery floor.</> - People of the Black Circle

Some sages argue that gold has properties that ward against creatures of the Outer Dark, but other, wiser sages have pointed out that wearing gold to ward off such creatures will attract the attention of a complete different class of unsavory being.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11055_ShortDesc", "A soft metal ingot that can be polished to a deep shine")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11055_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Do you think he is dead?' she asked, with seeming irrelevancy.
He did not ask her to whom she referred.

'I believe so. Silver and fire are both deadly to evil spirits, and he got a belly-full of both.'</> - The Black Stranger
Too weak to create effective weapons, silver is primarily for currency, ornamentation and the backing of polished mirrors. 
Silver can be effective against demonic creatures and spirits. Many a mercenary always keeps a single silver coin with them to ward off curses and dark creatures.

This metal can be smelted and used to forge weapons, but any such weapon will break after anything more than a single hit.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11056_ShortDesc", "A soft feather, used in fletching and cushioning")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11056_LongDesc", "Used primarily in the creation of arrows and for stuffing cushions, feathers come in all sizes and colors. Soft, downy feathers plucked from the breast of an animal are the best for cushioning, while stiffer feather taken from the tail of a bird are more useful for keeping arrows true in the air.\n\nThese feathers are taken from the wild birds that roam the Exiled Lands - so ferocious, but oh so delicious as well.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11057_ShortDesc", "The untreated skin of a beast")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11057_LongDesc", "The extremely thick hide of a Rhino. Sought after for their horns and skins, rhinos are prized by hunters throughout Stygia.

Due to their aggressive nature many hunters are lost every year. Sometimes perhaps it is better to leave the Rhino with their skin, than risk losing your own.

Taken from any number of wild beasts, hide can be processed into leather using a tannery.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11058_ShortDesc", "The pelt of a Hyena")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11058_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then he found something else to make him wonder. Among the furs on the dais was a gorgeous spotted skin, whose predominant hue was golden. It was not a clever copy, but the skin of an actual beast. And that beast, Conan knew, had been extinct for at least a thousand years; it was the great golden leopard which figures so prominently in Hyborian legendry, and which the ancient artists delighted to portray in pigments and marble.</> - The Devil in Iron

Pelts, skinned from beasts, with warm or tough or luxuriant fur, are among the earliest materials man has turned to clothing. To wear the skins of creatures the gods left less exposed to the elements - to take on their strength.

Pelts, even scabby and half-rotted ones, are prized by both the savage and the civilized.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11059_ShortDesc", "Where?")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11059_LongDesc", "Where elephant hide? Me not see elephant hiding here? You silly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11060_ShortDesc", "The sleek pelt of a large cat")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11060_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then he found something else to make him wonder. Among the furs on the dais was a gorgeous spotted skin, whose predominant hue was golden. It was not a clever copy, but the skin of an actual beast. And that beast, Conan knew, had been extinct for at least a thousand years; it was the great golden leopard which figures so prominently in Hyborian legendry, and which the ancient artists delighted to portray in pigments and marble.</> - The Devil in Iron

Pelts, skinned from beasts, with warm or tough or luxuriant fur, are among the earliest materials man has turned to clothing. To wear the skins of creatures the gods left less exposed to the elements - to take on their strength.

Pelts, such as this one taken from a panther, speak to the skill and strength of the hunter.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11061_ShortDesc", "The hairy pelt of a bear")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11061_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then he found something else to make him wonder. Among the furs on the dais was a gorgeous spotted skin, whose predominant hue was golden. It was not a clever copy, but the skin of an actual beast. And that beast, Conan knew, had been extinct for at least a thousand years; it was the great golden leopard which figures so prominently in Hyborian legendry, and which the ancient artists delighted to portray in pigments and marble.</> - The Devil in Iron

Pelts, skinned from beasts, with warm or tough or luxuriant fur, are among the earliest materials man has turned to clothing. To wear the skins of creatures the gods left less exposed to the elements - to take on their strength.

Pelts, such as this one taken from a bear, communicate strength, prowess and primal nature of the beast.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11062_ShortDesc", "Pieces of exoskeleton ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11062_LongDesc", "Scorpions and insects are covered in a hardened outer shell that provides them with some protection against the elements. Due to the extremely large size of these creatures in the Exiled Lands, their chitin can be harvested and used to all manner of purposes.\n\nThe harvesting is, of course, the difficult part. A man-sized scorpion is no laughing matter.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11063_ShortDesc", "The membranous skin of a bat")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11063_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There were grisly feasts beneath the moon, across whose red disk a bat-like shadow incessantly swept.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Though bat-skins are sought after by warlocks and witches, they find little traffic among the common merchants of Hyboria. 

In the Exiled Lands, the bat demons - once used by the Giant-kings as messengers and transport - have turned feral, nesting in the rooves and high places of the land. Their skins might be large enough to use for some purpose.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11064_ShortDesc", "Black glass formed from lava flows")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11064_LongDesc", "A sharp-edged, glassy stone. Not easily worked like iron or steel, obsidian can still be made into ridiculously brittle weapons.\n\nLegend persists that obsidian weapons are very powerful against certain undead creatures, but serious scholars insist that this was a lie perpetuated by the troubadour Grey Rain Rant Martinous in his well-known Ballad of Flame and Snow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11065_ShortDesc", "A silver coin")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11065_LongDesc", "This coin is made of silver. \nThese coins are of dubious mercantile value but can probably be melted down to obtain base metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11066_ShortDesc", "A gold coin")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11066_LongDesc", "This coin is made of gold.\nThese coins are of dubious mercantile value but can probably be melted down to obtain base metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11067_ShortDesc", "A pouch of silver dust")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11067_LongDesc", "Silver can be effective against demonic creatures and spirits. Many a mercenary always keeps a single silver coin with them to ward off curses and dark creatures.\n\nSilver dust is used in alchemical potions to create a wide-range of effects.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11068_ShortDesc", "A pouch of gold dust")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11068_LongDesc", "Gold has many properties considered desirable by alchemists, so it is always a hard decision for them to decide whether they should grind their gold into dust or use it to purchase more mundane ingredients.\n\nOver the years there have been plenty of alchemists who tried to have it both ways - and found themselves on the execution block for debasing the currency, a crime which kings and taxmen take very seriously.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11069_ShortDesc", "The pelt of a canine")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11069_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Then he found something else to make him wonder. Among the furs on the dais was a gorgeous spotted skin, whose predominant hue was golden. It was not a clever copy, but the skin of an actual beast. And that beast, Conan knew, had been extinct for at least a thousand years; it was the great golden leopard which figures so prominently in Hyborian legendry, and which the ancient artists delighted to portray in pigments and marble.</> - The Devil in Iron\n\nPelts, skinned from beasts, with warm or tough or luxuriant fur, are among the earliest materials man has turned to clothing. To wear the skins of creatures the gods left less exposed to the elements - to take on their strength.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11070_ShortDesc", "A standard mixture used to enhance and vivify potions")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11070_LongDesc", "Every alchemist has their own signature base, a set of ingredients that, when combined, are said to up the efficacy of their potions and tinctures.\n\nThis base, created by combining various ingredients scattered across the Exiled Lands, will serve to enhance the process of creating new compounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11071_ShortDesc", "A white, bonelike material from the tusks and teeth of animals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11071_LongDesc", "Like cultures and customs, the value of ivory depends upon the kingdom where it is seen.

In the Hyborian kingdoms, where elephants and other creatures are rare, it is a tangible sign of both wealth and power. In the Black Kingdoms, it is common - few warriors exist in those lands who do not possess an ivory handled dagger or jewelry.

It is a great source of trade between the north and the south - indeed it could be said that ivory is the primary reason that merchants dare make the dangerous journey along the Black Coast to trade for it in Kush.

The great herds of elephants which roam the Black Kingdoms are hunted daily for their tusks and there is no reason for men to suspect that the creatures will not continue to roam forever.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11072_ShortDesc", "The claws of some unfortunate beast")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11072_LongDesc", "These claws were harvested from the limbs of some poor creature. Hopefully it was dead, otherwise, somewhere out there in the wilderness there is a panther struggling frantically to maintain its grip on a tree, a bear casually slapping a deer on the rump or a very confused pack of wolves sliding across an icy lake.\n\nClaws can be ground into bone meal in a Grinder.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11073_ShortDesc", "An ornate key that fits any number of chests")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11073_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The chest forged in unholy fires among the flaming mountains of Khrosha; the metal no chisel can cut. How many treasures has it borne, across the width and the breadth of the world! But no such treasure as it now holds.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThis key is designed to fit a series of chests that are hidden across the breadth of the Exiled Lands. Rumor holds that they hold legendary treasures stolen from across the lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11074_ShortDesc", "A floating foundation")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11074_LongDesc", "This wooden pontoon can be placed on water and used as a basis for building. It is worth noting, however, that unlike building foundations pontoons cannot be stacked vertically.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11075_ShortDesc", "A mold for minting perfectly rounded coins ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11075_LongDesc", "Minting a currency is a crime punishable by death in almost all of the kingdoms of the Hyborian age. Kings are loathe to give up the power to regulate the currency of the kingdoms.\n\nThere was one attempt, years past, to make an independent currency built around the principles of free exchange and free markets. Unfortunately, the necromancer who invented the idea was executed before it could take root and his crypt-o-currency was forgotten.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11076_ShortDesc", "A handful of decomposed organic matter")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11076_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?

Carrying around piles of stinking decomposing matter, however, is probably not the most exciting part of farming. 

This compost can be used in planters to encourage planted seeds to grow strong and healthy.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11077_ShortDesc", "A handful of odorous, yet powerful, matter")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11077_LongDesc", "This compost is particularly potent for growing living things. The addition of blood and ash to the regular organic matter seems to have stimulated a particularly strong reaction.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11078_ShortDesc", "A mixture of fine and coarse bone grindings")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11078_LongDesc", "Kill everything, waste nothing is an adage of vital meaning to the tribes of Hyrkanian nomads who roam the steppes east of Turan. Out on the grasslands, every resource is vital, including the bones and claws of their kills which are ground down into bone meal.\n\nBone meal can be added to compost to improve its composition and, unappetizing as it sounds, it can also be used in some food recipes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11079_ShortDesc", "The crimson hued fluid of life")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11079_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan set his teeth and drove the sword deep. Blood streamed over the blade and his hand, and the monster started convulsively, then lay back quite still.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Blood is an inevitable part of life in the Exiled Lands - splattered on the weapons and clothing of friend and foe, running from the victorious blade, soaked in the bandages of the wounded.

There is a power in blood, not just in the foul sorceries of black mages, but in the blood of ordinary men and women.

Blood can be mixed into compost to increase the potency of the mixture and bring additional life from this side effect of death.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11080_ShortDesc", "Plucked from gently waving frost lotus")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11080_LongDesc", "Unlike the other flowers of this family, the frost lotus has no towering reputation for strange mystical effects. It is possible that alchemists have simply not discovered the best possible use of this blossom - further experimentation is the only way to find out.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11081_ShortDesc", "Seeds of the frost lotus")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11081_LongDesc", "Unlike the other flowers of this family, the frost lotus has no towering reputation for strange mystical effects. It is possible that alchemists have simply not discovered the best possible use of this blossom - further experimentation is the only way to find out.\n\nThese seeds can be placed in a planter and together with fertilizer will grow a plant over time. These plants may then be collected or left as decoration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11082_ShortDesc", "Seeds of the yellow lotus")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11082_LongDesc", "While the black lotus is feared for its deadly effect, the yellow lotus is known for its ability to cause visions and hallucinations of great import.

Those who lose themselves in the lotus dreams can have a difficult path back, but eternal renewal is worth the risk.

These seeds can be placed in a planter and together with fertilizer will grow a plant over time. These plants may then be collected or left as decoration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11083_ShortDesc", "Plucked from gently waving purple lotus")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11083_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It is steeped in the juice of the purple lotus which grows in the ghost-haunted swamps of southern Stygia, said the magician.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

The purple lotus plant, which grows in the southern swamps of Stygia, is a favorite weapon of sorcerers. The juice of the plant causes a temporary paralysis - a seemingly sorcerous effect that does not require the actual use of sorcery.

As such it has become extremely popular as a blade coating and for treating the small needles used in traps and trick rings.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11084_ShortDesc", "A small bag of purple lotus powder")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11084_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It is steeped in the juice of the purple lotus which grows in the ghost-haunted swamps of southern Stygia, said the magician.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

The purple lotus plant, which grows in the southern swamps of Stygia, is a favorite weapon of sorcerers. The juice of the plant causes a temporary paralysis - a seemingly sorcerous effect that does not require the actual use of sorcery.

What effect the dried powder of the flower will have, is unknown.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11085_ShortDesc", "Seeds of the purple lotus")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11085_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It is steeped in the juice of the purple lotus which grows in the ghost-haunted swamps of southern Stygia, said the magician.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

The purple lotus plant, which grows in the southern swamps of Stygia, is a favorite weapon of sorcerers. The juice of the plant causes a temporary paralysis - a seemingly sorcerous effect that does not require the actual use of sorcery.

These seeds can be placed in a planter and together with fertilizer will grow a plant over time. These plants may then be collected or left as decoration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11086_ShortDesc", "Plucked from deadly black lotus")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11086_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The next instant, with appalling suddenness, the jungle waved and dimmed out before his eyes; he did not hear the screams that burst out awfully not far away, as his knees collapsed, letting him pitch limply to the earth. Above his prostrate form the great black blossoms nodded in the windless air.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

The black lotus is a much feared, oft-discussed, plant. It is said that the scent of the flowers brings mad, blighted dreams that trouble all but the blackest of souls. The juice of the black lotus is death, an instant plunge into darkness from which one can never recover.

It is rumored that the sorcerers of the Black Ring use the Black lotus to recover their necromantic powers. Few know the secrets of the alchemy involved and there are few who dare to experiment with such a deadly substance.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11087_ShortDesc", "A small bag of black lotus powder ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11087_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then Taurus brought the mouth of the tube to his lips and blew powerfully. A long jet of yellowish powder shot from the other end of the tube and billowed out instantly in a thick green-yellow cloud that settled over the shrubbery, blotting out the glaring eyes.</> - Tower of the Elephant

The black lotus is a much feared, oft-discussed, plant. It is said that the scent of the flowers brings mad, blighted dreams that trouble all but the blackest of souls. The juice of the black lotus is death, an instant plunge into darkness from which one can never recover.

This powder is known to be deadly to animals when blown into their faces, though with the wrong wind, such an attack can prove deadlier to the attacker.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11088_ShortDesc", "Seeds of the black lotus")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11088_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The next instant, with appalling suddenness, the jungle waved and dimmed out before his eyes; he did not hear the screams that burst out awfully not far away, as his knees collapsed, letting him pitch limply to the earth. Above his prostrate form the great black blossoms nodded in the windless air.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

It is rumored that the sorcerers of the Black Ring use the Black lotus to recover their necromantic powers. Few know the secrets of the alchemy involved and there are few who dare to experiment with such a deadly substance.

These seeds can be placed in a planter and together with fertilizer will grow a plant over time. These plants may then be collected or left as decoration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11089_ShortDesc", "Plucked from gently waving golden lotus")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11089_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was no dagger in her fingers; they grasped a stalk of golden lotus, the crushed blossoms drooping on the bruised stem.</> - People of the Black Circle

Known for its healing properties, golden lotus has been rumored to be able to mend broken bones, heal scars and even unnaturally extend the life of those who drink it.

Perhaps for this reason, golden lotus is extremely rare.")

column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11091_ShortDesc", "Plucked from the gray lotus plant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11091_LongDesc", "The Grey Lotus plant is rumored to grow only in the swamps of the dead, beyond the land of Khitai. A powder made from these plants is known to drive men into a berserker rage, giving them inhuman strength and brutality - and no capacity for mercy.\n\nAny who use it do so at the risk of not only their lives, but the lives of their friends and family.")

These seeds can be placed in a planter and together with fertilizer will grow a plant over time. These plants may then be collected or left as decoration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11094_ShortDesc", "Seeds that can be planted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11094_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11100_ShortDesc", "A cutting taken from a Phykos plant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11100_LongDesc", "Underwater plants cannot be simply grown from seeds. They need to be cut, and the living sample placed in a special type of tank.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11101_ShortDesc", "A length of vine ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11101_LongDesc", "This length of fibrous vine, cut in the swamps of the Exiled Lands. These vines can be broken down into tough plant fibers.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11102_ShortDesc", "Cold, lifeless ashes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11102_LongDesc", "What was burned to create these ashes is not apparent but mixing them into compost increase its potency. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11103_ShortDesc", "A stone inscribed with a bizarre symbol")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11103_LongDesc", "This small piece of stone is inscribed with a symbol that seems to slide away from the eye that beholds it. There is something dark and wonderful about the lines and swirls that make up the shape. This could be offered up to the Archives in order to obtain ancient wisdom.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11104_ShortDesc", "A mold for casting bracelets from precious metals ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11104_LongDesc", "Jewelry is considered a sign of status and wealth. This holds true from the most primitive tribes to the most civilized. One need only glance at a Shemite merchant, arms and legs covered in golden trinkets, to understand the power that jewelry conveys.\n\nThis simple mold can be used to make bracelets from precious metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11105_ShortDesc", "A mold for casting anklets from precious metals ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11105_LongDesc", "Jewelry is considered a sign of status and wealth. This holds true from the most primitive tribes to the most civilized. One need only glance at a Shemite merchant, arms and legs covered in golden trinkets, to understand the power that jewelry conveys.\n\nThis simple mold can be used to make anklets from precious metals.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11106_LongDesc", "Jewelry is considered a sign of status and wealth. This holds true from the most primitive tribes to the most civilized. One need only glance at a Shemite merchant, arms and legs covered in golden trinkets, to understand the power that jewelry conveys.\n\nThis simple mold can be used to make circlets from precious metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11107_ShortDesc", "A mold for casting earrings from precious metals ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11107_LongDesc", "Jewelry is considered a sign of status and wealth. This holds true from the most primitive tribes to the most civilized. One need only glance at a Shemite merchant, arms and legs covered in golden trinkets, to understand the power that jewelry conveys.\n\nThis simple mold can be used to make earrings from precious metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11108_ShortDesc", "Wood treated with resin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11108_LongDesc", "Wood is an abundant source of fuel and building material.
Readily available and easily shaped with the right tools, wood is ubiquitous in the weapons and buildings of primitive tribes and mighty nations.

Wood allows for the creation of fire and its easy transport.

This wood has been treated with resin, making it stronger and more weather resistant.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11109_ShortDesc", "Seeds that can be planted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11109_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11110_ShortDesc", "Seeds that can be planted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11110_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11111_ShortDesc", "A manifestation of unfulfilled desire")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11111_LongDesc", "The priests and priestesses of Derketo are well trained in the skills of pleasure and pain. They walk their congregations down an exquisite line between release and ecstasy, and their sweat-filled temples are filled with the moans and exultations of those who know the touch of the goddess.\n\nSuch pleasure, both fulfilled and unfulfilled, leaves a physical residue. The worshippers of Derketo offer it up to their goddess as proof that her bidding is being done on this earth.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11112_ShortDesc", "Armor Scraps collected from the Warmaker\'s retreat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11112_LongDesc", "These armor-scraps, while broken and rusted could be used to put together a complete armor, if one had enough of them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11113_ShortDesc", "Seeds that can be planted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11113_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11114_ShortDesc", "A handle required for crafting high end weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11114_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting blades, heads and shields grows stronger, it is important that the other elements of the weapon are strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis handle is functional and will prevent weapons from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11115_ShortDesc", "A handle required for crafting high end weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11115_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting blades, heads and shields grows stronger, it is important that the other elements of the weapon are strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis handle is functional and will prevent weapons from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11116_ShortDesc", "A shield frame required for crafting high end shields")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11116_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting blades, heads and shields grows stronger, it is important that the other elements of the weapon are strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis frame is functional and will prevent shields from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11117_ShortDesc", "A strengthened length of string required for crafting high end bows and crossbows")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11117_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting blades, heads and shields grows stronger, it is important that the other elements of the weapon are strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis length of string is functional and will prevent weapons from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")
