column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11118_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting blades, heads and shields grows stronger, it is important that the other elements of the weapon are strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis handle is functional and will prevent weapons from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11119_ShortDesc", "A handle required for crafting high end weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11119_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting blades, heads and shields grows stronger, it is important that the other elements of the weapon are strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis handle is functional and will prevent weapons from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11120_ShortDesc", "A handle required for crafting high end weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11120_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting blades, heads and shields grows stronger, it is important that the other elements of the weapon are strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis handle is functional and will prevent weapons from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11121_ShortDesc", "A small bag of frost lotus powder")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11121_LongDesc", "Unlike the other flowers of this family, the frost lotus has no towering reputation for strange mystical effects. It is possible that alchemists have simply not discovered the best possible use of this blossom - further experimentation is the only way to find out.\n\nWhat effect the dried powder of the flower will have, is unknown.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11122_ShortDesc", "A small bag of yellow lotus powder")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11122_LongDesc", "While the black lotus is feared for its deadly effect, the yellow lotus is known for its ability to cause visions and hallucinations of great import.

Those who lose themselves in the lotus dreams can have a difficult path back, but eternal renewal is worth the risk.

What effect the dried powder of the flower will have, is unknown.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11123_ShortDesc", "A small bag of golden lotus powder")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11123_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was no dagger in her fingers; they grasped a stalk of golden lotus, the crushed blossoms drooping on the bruised stem.</> - People of the Black Circle

Known for its healing properties, golden lotus has been rumored to be able to mend broken bones, heal scars and even unnaturally extend the life of those who drink it.

What effect the dried powder of the flower will have, is unknown.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11124_ShortDesc", "A blossom plucked from the crimson lotus")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11124_LongDesc", "There are many varieties of lotus in the world, but the Exiled Lands seems to bring forth a few unique varieties. The Crimson Lotus grows on the site of ancient battlefields - it seems to thrive in soil that has been soaked in blood.\n\nWhat special properties does it have? It will take an avid (or foolhardy) alchemist to find out.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11125_ShortDesc", "A small bag of crimson lotus powder")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11125_LongDesc", "There are many varieties of lotus in the world, but the Exiled Lands seems to bring forth a few unique varieties. The Crimson Lotus grows on the site of ancient battlefields - it seems to thrive in soil that has been soaked in blood.\n\nWhat effect the dried powder of the flower will have, is unknown.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11126_ShortDesc", "Seeds of the crimson lotus")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11126_LongDesc", "There are many varieties of lotus in the world, but the Exiled Lands seems to bring forth a few unique varieties. The Crimson Lotus grows on the site of ancient battlefields - it seems to thrive in soil that has been soaked in blood.\n\nThese seeds can be placed in a planter and together with fertilizer will grow a plant over time. These plants may then be collected or left as decoration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11127_ShortDesc", "Black liquid that reeks of the outer dark")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11127_LongDesc", "This black ooze, harvested from the corpse of a demonic entity, steams slightly when exposed to air.
Blood is used to increase the potency of the blasphemous rituals of both priests and sorcerers. And this is particularly potent blood.
The nature of demons is hotly disputed by scholars. Some suggest that they are simply remnants of elder races that stalked the earth before mankind, while others insist that they are formless creatures from the outer void given form by the incantation of vile sorceries.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11128_ShortDesc", "Seeds that can be planted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11128_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11129_ShortDesc", "A core required for crafting lances")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11129_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting handles, tips and guards grows stronger, it is important that the core of the weapon is strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis handle is functional and will prevent weapons from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11497_ShortDesc", "Flimsy metal scraps")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11497_LongDesc", "These scraps are not useful for anything except for being smelted in a furnace.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11498_ShortDesc", "A piece of reforged Eldarium")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11498_LongDesc", "Recovered from a vault and reforged with hardened steel, this is the closest approximation to the vault materials that it is possible to make.\n\nIt is almost alien in its qualities, being easier to work than steel and yet harder than any other substance found in the natural world.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11499_ShortDesc", "Heavily decayed chunks of Eldarium")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11499_LongDesc", "This decayed chunk of metal was recovered from the interior of one of the vaults on the Isle of Siptah. The origin and construction of this metal is unknown and the secret of its smithing has long been forgotten. \n\nWith the right process, however, it is possible to salvage useable metal from this decayed piece.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11500_ShortDesc", "A chunk of stone pulsing with corruption")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11500_LongDesc", "Thousands of years of sorcerous rituals have left their essence embedded deeply in this stone. It seethes with dark intent - but perhaps that can be useful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11501_ShortDesc", "Basic iron ingot for crude metalworking")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11501_LongDesc", "The ability to work iron is a step along the road from savagery to civilization. The streets of the great cities of the world resound with the ring of hammer on anvil a song to the march of progress.\nIron weapons and armor offer superior protection, but the additional weight means carrying less supplies.\nIron can be treated with Steelfire in a Furnace to produce steel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11502_ShortDesc", "An alloy that is stronger and less brittle than iron")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11502_LongDesc", "Barring some enchantment, steel is the strongest metal alloy available for the construction of weapons. The crafting of steel requires iron and Steelfire, a peculiar additive made from Tar and Brimstone.\nThe smiths of Akbitana in Shem are the finest in the world and a weapon made of Akbitanan steel is considered to be unbreakable. Due to their great demand, it is rare to find a Akbitanan weapon outside of Shem.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11504_ShortDesc", "Toxin gland taken from the monstrous scorpion queen")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11504_LongDesc", "The most potent venom in the Exiled Lands, carefully extracted from the venom glands of the Scorpion Queen.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11551_ShortDesc", "Brittle and breakable, glass is best used for ornamentation")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11551_LongDesc", "Only the wealthy can afford to ornament their houses in glass, even though creating glass is a simple process. Glass offers protection from the elements and a view of what is occurring outside, at the risk of being easily shattered.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12001_ShortDesc", "Assorted stalks, leaves and sprigs torn from plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12001_LongDesc", "The most basic materials that can be gathered by hand from plants. These fibers can be woven into rough clothing, but it will only provide simple protection against the elements.\nAnything woven from such crude material cannot be expected to stop a swinging blade.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12003_ShortDesc", "Spider silk - soft, strong and lightweight")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12003_LongDesc", "Harvested from the webs of spiders, gossamer can be spun into a durable, strong thread.
Gathering gossamer would require weeks were it not for the presence of extremely large spiders in the Exiled Lands. Their webs are large enough that gossamer gathering can be a profitable enterprise.
It is not known what causes the spider in the region to grow to such an extreme size, but enterprising Stygians have been harvesting gossamer here for centuries.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12011_ShortDesc", "The untreated skin of a beast")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12011_LongDesc", "Taken from any number of wild beasts, hide can be processed into leather using a tannery.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12012_ShortDesc", "Some creatures have thicker skins than others")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12012_LongDesc", "Large beasts have developed thicker skins for defence against predators. This thickened skin, while harder to work, provides a superior leather. \nWorshippers of the beast-god, Jhebbal Sag have been known to clothe themselves in the hides of ferocious predators as a symbol of their pact.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12013_ShortDesc", "Hide harvested from a reptile")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12013_LongDesc", "Along the reaches of the Styx, the great crocodiles of Stygia are feared as man-eaters and messengers of the gods. Although not as bound to the Stygian religion as the great snakes that haunt the blood-mad streets of Khemi, crocodiles are still revered and considered sacred.\nPoachers and hunters from the Black Kingdoms to the south, however, do not share this reverence for the crocodile and willingly hunt them for their skins which make a fine leather.\nThis reptile skin might have been taken from a crocodile or a large lizard.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12511_ShortDesc", "Tanned hide that is commonly used for lightweight armors")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12511_LongDesc", "Supple material that offers enhanced protection. Leather can be stiff and difficult to work if it has not been correctly treated, but there is a fine line between softening the leather too far and having it lose its protective properties.
Leather will help to stop the claws and fangs of a beast, but a determined foe will be able to break through the material.
Used to create armors at an Armorers Bench
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12512_ShortDesc", "Offers a higher degree of protection than regular leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12512_LongDesc", "Offering better protection than regular leather, but at the cost of flexibility.
Thickened leather requires regular oiling to prevent it from becoming inflexible and preventing movement.
Kordavan leather is famed for its pliability and durability, but to learn the secret of its durability would require access to the tanneries of the Zingaran capital.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12513_ShortDesc", "A strong, light thread spun from gossamer")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12513_LongDesc", "Silk is a valuable commodity in the Hyborian kingdoms and it flows from Khitai in the east and Stygia in the south. Khitan silk is drawn from silkworms whereas Stygian silk is harvested from the giant spiders that inhabit the dark reaches of the southern lands.\nKhitan silk is prized for the clinging, sensual fabric that it creates. It is very tolerant of dyes and holds brilliant color. Any nobleman of note has at least one outfit of Khitan silk.\nStygian silk is stronger and more durable, offering greater protection at the cost of a coarser weave. Dyes tend to fade quickly but the tenacity of the fabric makes it a favorite among the merchant class.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12514_ShortDesc", "A viscous, foul smelling fluid collected from arthropods")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12514_LongDesc", "Medicine men and herbalists tend to pay well for the ichors of exotic and dangerous species killed in the wilds, but it has other, hidden properties.\nIn Stygia, ichor is mixed with fibers and used to harden stone under very high heat, adding a glaze to the stone that makes it impervious to normal weapons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12515_ShortDesc", "A strong, light thread spun from gossamer")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12515_LongDesc", "Silk is a valuable commodity in the Hyborian kingdoms and it flows from Khitai in the east and Stygia in the south. Khitan silk is drawn from silkworms whereas Stygian silk is harvested from the giant spiders that inhabit the dark reaches of the southern lands.\nKhitan silk is prized for the clinging, sensual fabric that it creates. It is very tolerant of dyes and holds brilliant color. Any nobleman of note has at least one outfit of Khitan silk.\nStygian silk is stronger and more durable, offering greater protection at the cost of a coarser weave. Dyes tend to fade quickly but the tenacity of the fabric makes it a favorite among the merchant class.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12516_ShortDesc", "Tanned hide that is commonly used for lightweight armors")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12516_LongDesc", "Supple material that offers enhanced protection. Leather can be stiff and difficult to work if it has not been correctly treated, but there is a fine line between softening the leather too far and having it lose its protective properties.
Leather will help to stop the claws and fangs of a beast, but a determined foe will be able to break through the material.
Used to create armors at an Armorers Bench
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13001_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from small beasts and fowl")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13001_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.
This flesh is harvested from small animals. It is not particularly filling or flavorful. 
Unless this meat is cooked quickly, it will spoil and become inedible.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13002_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from common wild animals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13002_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.
This flesh has been harvested from large game. It is easy to cook and full of flavour.
Unless this meat is cooked quickly, it will spoil and become inedible.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13003_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from exotic animals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13003_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.
This flesh is taken from one of the exotic creatures that roam the Exiled Lands. The effect of this meat is particularly potent, but whether this boost is due to the rare flavour or is an aftereffect of the thrilling hunt is a matter for sages to discuss.
Unless this meat is cooked quickly, it will spoil and become inedible.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13011_ShortDesc", "A large nutritious meal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13011_LongDesc", "Many eggs, amongst others the Shaleback eggs, are considered a rare delicacy in the civilized lands. Anybody who has seen an enraged adult Shaleback up close can understand why they remain so.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13012_ShortDesc", "Disgusting, yet filling")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13012_LongDesc", "For the strong of stomach, these grubs offer a both food and moisture in the midst of the desert")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13013_ShortDesc", "These will keep starvation at bay. Barely.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13013_LongDesc", "To the starving, a handful of insects can be enough to stave off hunger for a while. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13014_ShortDesc", "A bite sized scorpion snack with extra sting")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13014_LongDesc", "A hard crunchy shell with a soft, satisfying center. These are considered a delicacy in some cultures.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13015_ShortDesc", "Small seeds taken from the foilage of the Exiled Lands")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13015_LongDesc", "These small seeds can be ground into a paste and made into a thin gruel. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13051_ShortDesc", "Flesh torn from other humans")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13051_LongDesc", "Consuming the flesh of men is a mark of savagery and desperation. Various demonic religious practices encourage ritual consumption while some tribes in the Black Kingdoms devour pieces of their fallen enemies in order to absorb their prowess and courage.\nThe desert men of Darfar are well known for their cannibalism. With their teeth filed to points and bizarre hairstyles of mud and twigs they are an intimidating sight - more so with the blood of a fresh kill drying on their chins.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13052_ShortDesc", "Eyes taken from a being of pure innocence")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13052_LongDesc", "It is said that all beings are born with light eyes, that darken when the world begins to stain them. These eyes, taken from a creature too young to know the evils of the world, contain a certain amount of power that can be called upon in occult rituals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13053_ShortDesc", "Flesh torn from other humans")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13053_LongDesc", "Consuming the flesh of men is a mark of savagery and desperation. Various demonic religious practices encourage ritual consumption while some tribes in the Black Kingdoms devour pieces of their fallen enemies in order to absorb their prowess and courage.\nThe desert men of Darfar are well known for their cannibalism. With their teeth filed to points and bizarre hairstyles of mud and twigs they are an intimidating sight - more so with the blood of a fresh kill drying on their chins.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13501_ShortDesc", "Cooked scraps of feral meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13501_LongDesc", "Tough, chewy meat that spoils quickly. Preferential to scavenged foods or raw meat, this gamy meat is hard on the teeth and the palate.\nThe taverns of the great cities are known using this type of meat for stewing though in Shadizar it is more likely to be cat or rat scraps that find their way into the pot.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13502_ShortDesc", "Cooked slab of succulent meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13502_LongDesc", "Juicy with the blood and fat of the kill, this universally life sustaining meal could as easily be found around the campfires of hunters from Vanaheim to the southern Black Kingdoms.\nFlavorful and filling, the only downside is the relative ease with which the meat becomes spoiled.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13503_ShortDesc", "A cooked haunch of exotic meat ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13503_LongDesc", "Taken from one of the more unusual beasts of the Exiled Lands, this mouth-watering meat is the height of culinary grace in this savage land.\nIn the great palaces of the Hyborian kingdoms noblemen hold lavish feasts where the reek of intrigue and exotic meats fill the smoky air. The quests that their servants undertake - and the dangers that they face - to obtain the near-mythical fare is the stuff of epicurean legend.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13540_ShortDesc", "A thin, foul-smelling gruel")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13540_LongDesc", "Made from plant seeds that have been ground into a paste and mixed with water, this thin and watery gruel is probably not enough to sustain an active adventurer. For thralls, however, it serves.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13550_ShortDesc", "The crushed bones and marrow of an otherworldly creature.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13550_LongDesc", "Taken from a dark creature summoned from the outer void, this ground up hunk of disgusting matter glows with an otherworldy energy.\nIt\'s probably useful for something, but eating it should be a last resort.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13597_ShortDesc", "Gruel that has turned green")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13597_LongDesc", "The only thing more disgusting than gruel, is spoiled gruel. This lumpy mixture of mold and clustered clumps of debris should not be eaten. By anything.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13598_ShortDesc", "A stinking mass of black matter")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13598_LongDesc", "Whatever this once belonged to, it is now unrecognizable. Any occult properties it may have once possessed are probably expired.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13599_ShortDesc", "Whatever this used to be, it is inedible now")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13599_LongDesc", "Meat which has begun to putrefy has an odor and flavour all of its own.\nEating it might stave off starvation, but at the price of becoming violently ill. Even carrion eaters shun putrid meat.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13600_ShortDesc", "The cooked flesh of the abysmal remnant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13600_LongDesc", "This foul-smelling, acidic meat does not look or smell appetizing even after being cooked. Considering the creature that it came from, and the environment where it was found, consuming this would be a foolhardy endeavor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13601_ShortDesc", "An offering to the bloody spectacle of battle")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13601_LongDesc", "Thousands of years past, when the Giant-kings ruled the land and the arena was active, there was a human gladiator named Tyros.\nTyros was a fighter such as the world had never seen - legend had it that he was a descendant of the legendary Kull of Atlantis.\nOne of the many names that were ascribed to Tyros during his gladiatorial career was that of Dragonslayer. It was said that the appearance of Tyros in the arena was enough to drive the beasts wild with rage. This offering, however, was the more likely cause. Before every battle it was burned on the sacrifice altar and the smoke from the offering was said to drive any within the arena into a mighty frenzy - perhaps even reaching across the boundary between life and death.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14001_ShortDesc", "This spiky plant has well known healing properties when made into a potion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14001_LongDesc", "A favorite of herbalists the world over, the leaves of this plant are highly sought after for their medicinal properties.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14101_ShortDesc", "Venom swollen glands harvested from serpents")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14101_LongDesc", "The serpents of the Exiled Lands vary in the potency of their venom from mildly irritating to lethal. 
The use of serpent venom for coating weapons before battle is a myth. Venom needs to be injected directly into the blood to have an effect and the act of plunging a weapon into a body is a far more efficient way to damage foes than to wait for a slow acting venom.
Alchemists and healers, however, do tout the efficacy of ingesting small amounts of venom to build an immunity. It is said that King Yezdigerd of Turan ritually ingests small amounts of many different poisons to build his protection against assassination attempts.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14102_ShortDesc", "Toxin gland taken from the monstrous reaper")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14102_LongDesc", "The Sand Reapers spit a venomous toxin that causes the skin to rot from the body on contact. Harvesting this toxin is a foolhardy but valuable undertaking.\nApplying this toxin to specially prepared grooved blades allows precise delivery of the toxin to enemies in melee.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14103_ShortDesc", "Toxin gland taken from the Scorpion Queen")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14103_LongDesc", "Harvesting this toxin is a foolhardy but valuable undertaking.\nApplying this toxin to specially prepared grooved blades allows precise delivery of the toxin to enemies in melee.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14149_ShortDesc", "A boon granted by Hanuman")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14149_LongDesc", "This multi-colored tincture can be consumed in order to get a random bonus to one attribute.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14150_ShortDesc", "Made from strange materials that dropped from the sky")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14150_LongDesc", "From the sky, a light will fall 
Bringing horrors to us all 
Shards of it can be consumed 
You may be blessed - or may be doomed")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14151_ShortDesc", "Plucked from gently waving lotus blossoms")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14151_LongDesc", "While the black lotus is feared for its deadly effect, the yellow lotus is known for its ability to cause visions and hallucinations of great import.\nThose who lose themselves in the lotus dreams can have a difficult path back, but eternal renewal is worth the risk.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14152_ShortDesc", "A composite of obsidian and steel")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14152_LongDesc", "Obsidian and steel that has been melded together by an expert blacksmith. Such a material retains the sharpness of the obsidian and the strength of the steel.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14155_ShortDesc", "Contains a number of basic materials")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14155_LongDesc", "Bearers are used to carry materials in order to resupply the war camps of their tribe.\n\nUse this package to open it up to gain the materials inside.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14156_ShortDesc", "Contains a number of basic materials")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14156_LongDesc", "Bearers are used to carry materials in order to resupply the war camps of their tribe.\n\nUse this package to open it up to gain the materials inside.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14157_ShortDesc", "Contains a number of basic materials")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14157_LongDesc", "Bearers are used to carry materials in order to resupply the war camps of their tribe.\n\nUse this package to open it up to gain the materials inside.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14158_ShortDesc", "Contains a number of basic materials")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14158_LongDesc", "Bearers are used to carry materials in order to resupply the war camps of their tribe.\n\nUse this package to open it up to gain the materials inside.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14171_ShortDesc", "Foul smelling yellow crystals used in dark rituals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14171_LongDesc", "Brimstone is one of the most sought after alchemical components due its application in a wide variety of concoctions.
Searing fumes make collecting it a difficult task and the bleached bones of those who did not adequately prepare serve as a grisly warning to others.
Combined with sticky tar, brimstone creates steelfire, which is a catalyst that hardens iron into steel.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14172_ShortDesc", "Thick black substance used for sealing wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14172_LongDesc", "Prized by alchemists and sailors alike, tar is a black oily substance derived from the dry heating of bark. It is a by-product of using bark in the tanning process.\nFrom the Vilayet to the Western Ocean, shipwrights know the value of tar as a water repellent. The legendary purple-sailed fleet of Turan owes the color to the unusual mix of tar and local chemicals used to soak the sailcloth.\nIn the gladiatorial arenas of Argos, tar is used to seal cuts and abrasions and ward off minor infections.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14173_ShortDesc", "A volatile mix of tar and brimstone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14173_LongDesc", "An unfortunate smith in Khoraja found himself homeless when his premises burned to the ground. Unable to explain the fire or its root cause, he nevertheless noticed that the steel he had been working on had survived the fire intact and was hardened beyond any metal that he had worked with before.\nBeing a cautious man, he experimented with different variations of the equipment in his newly rebuilt smithy until he reached the conclusion that tar from his poorly sealed roof had dripped into his bloomery and tainted the brimstone that he was using as a catalyst.\nHe gave his new catalyst the fanciful name of Steelfire and made a great deal of money before other smiths were able to replicate his results.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14174_ShortDesc", "A small length of twine")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14174_LongDesc", "Created by twisting lengths of fiber together to create a sturdy length of string, twine is used for binding the most primitive weapons and items together.\nThe advantage of twine is that it is easily created from scavenged ingredients, such as plant fiber, but it\'s tendency to unravel at unfortunate times makes anything crafted with it inherently fragile.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14175_ShortDesc", "Taken from the tresses of dead women")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14175_LongDesc", "In Zamoria, there was a city ruled by a sorcerer named Yara in his fabulous dwelling known only as the Tower of the Elephant. Yara had a dark reputation, but he was also rumored to be the keeper of a wonderful treasure known only as the Heart of the Elephant.\nNobody knows precisely what happened to Yara, but his tower collapsed into rubble and among the rubble was found a coil of rope woven from hair. Though none knew its purpose, many speculated that the hair for the rope was taken from dead women, in accordance with a ritual found in the dread Book of Skelos, which would make it incredibly strong.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14181_ShortDesc", "Dust stolen from a tomb")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14181_LongDesc", "Those who rob the dead are either desperate, brave or possessed of such dark power that they no longer fear the dead.\nThe dust stolen from the tombs of dead Stygians is said to cause blindness when flung into the eyes of an opponent. It has darker uses that are detailed in the blasphemous Book of Skelos.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14182_ShortDesc", "Black liquid that reeks of the outer dark")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14182_LongDesc", "This black ooze, harvested from the corpse of a demonic entity, steams slightly when exposed to air.
Blood is used to increase the potency of the blasphemous rituals of both priests and sorcerers. And this is particularly potent blood.
The nature of demons is hotly disputed by scholars. Some suggest that they are simply remnants of elder races that stalked the earth before mankind, while others insist that they are formless creatures from the outer void given form by the incantation of vile sorceries.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14183_ShortDesc", "A volatile powder created by mashing various alchemical components")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14183_LongDesc", "Alchemists in the west first discovered this wondrous powder through a crumbling manuscript that came with a caravan from Khitai. \nThrough much experimentation and loss of limb and life, they eventually stablized the formula with localized ingredients. Combined with other ingredients, Dragonpowder becomes a potent explosive - though many see it as a form of sorcery and refuse to use it in battle.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14184_ShortDesc", "A powder crafted from foul ingredients by the Darfari")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14184_LongDesc", "This powder corrupts absolutely and is used in rituals involving the dead. It can be used to ritually infuse bones in order to raise the dead and corrupt the living.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14185_ShortDesc", "An eye from the Abysmal Remnant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14185_LongDesc", "This eye seems to glow with an inhuman intelligence. The creature from which it was taken was of supernatural origin and this large, almost hypnotic eye explains how it could lure prey close enough to feast.\nWhile the properties of the eye seem to have passed with the death of the creature, it will still make for an impressive trophy.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14186_ShortDesc", "A fang from the Abysmal Remnant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14186_LongDesc", "This fang, harvested from the corpse of the Abysmal Remnant, is made of an extremely hard substance. Due to the acidic environment in which the creature lived the material has developed several properties beyond regular ivory or bone which mean that it is durable.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14187_ShortDesc", "Flesh harvested from the Abysmal Remnant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14187_LongDesc", "This foul-smelling, acidic meat does not look or smell appetizing.\nConsidering the creature that it came from, and the environment where it was found, consuming this would be a foolhardy endeavor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14190_ShortDesc", "A gray flower used to dye clothing")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14190_LongDesc", "This common flower is used by Hyrkanians to dye their felt yurts. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14191_ShortDesc", "A plant with flowers of startling color")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14191_LongDesc", "Cultivated in Stygia, the petals of this plant produce a brightly colored dye which the Stygians use for decorating ceremonial clothing and armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14192_ShortDesc", "An orange, water-dwelling plant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14192_LongDesc", "Plucked from the bottom of a lake or river, this plant can be used to produce a bright orange dye that sets in even the most stubborn of material.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14193_ShortDesc", "A small insect with brightly colored innards")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14193_LongDesc", "These small insects live and feed on cacti. They can be prepared into a bright red dye for use in coloring textiles. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14194_ShortDesc", "A bush with small berries")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14194_LongDesc", "The berries of true mandrake must be taken from the resting place of a dead man by the light of the moon. False mandrake berries are much simpler to harvest and can be used to create a purple dye. \nSome have suggested that the intense blooming of False Mandrake along the banks of the Vilayet during spring is a simple explanation for the fabled purple sails of the Turanian fleet. However, alchemists argue that the purple comes from the properties of the pitch found in the region.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14195_ShortDesc", "A pile of...something that glows")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14195_LongDesc", "What this is, where it comes from and how it got here are a mystery. What matters is that it can be used in the creation of a cyan dye.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14196_ShortDesc", "A bile gland taken from a supernatural creature")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14196_LongDesc", "When the sandstorm comes howling across the Exiled Lands, it is accompanied by the strange screams of the beasts that inhabit it. What they are and why they follow the storms is one of the many mysteries of the Exiled Lands. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14197_ShortDesc", "A glowing gum-like substance")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14197_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The tunnel debouched into a wide room before the moonlight played out, an empty cavern of no great dimensions, but with a lofty, vaulted roof, glowing with a phosphorescent encrustation, which, as Conan knew, was a common phenomenon in that part of the world.</> 
Jewels of Gwahlur

Some shipwrecked Zingaran mercenaries stumbled into Khemi, wild-eyed with a tale of beautiful mermaids who lured half of their company to their death on the shallow reefs off the coast.

Though the sailors were adamant that the naked, beautiful women were fish from the waist down, their reports of "shining smiles" led scholars to suspect that they were native Kushite women chewing a glowing paste that allowed them to prolong their time underwater.

The existence of this paste is well known among the shamans of the Black Kingdoms, though it is rare in the north where the plants that are used in its production do not commonly grow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14199_ShortDesc", "Flower of a magenta hue")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14199_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Send my soul clean to Asura!\'</> - The People of the Black Circle\n\nThis tall flower originated in Vendhya, but through trade and happenstance, this hardy bloom can now be found growing in many places the world over. Its magenta hue is much sought after for dyes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14200_ShortDesc", "A flask for storing liquids")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14200_LongDesc", "Glass is a fragile substance most often used by nobles and rich merchants for mirrors and windows. Alchemists also prize it for its ability to store volatile concoctions and their ability to observe reactions within the glass as they experiment. Experienced alchemists have hundreds of such flasks, filled with exotic materials from across the world. Less experienced alchemists are probably dead because they stored their concoctions in a less adequate container.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14201_ShortDesc", "A glass flask filled with water")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14201_LongDesc", "Glass is a fragile substance most often used by nobles and rich merchants for mirrors and windows. Alchemists also prize it for its ability to store volatile concoctions and their ability to observe reactions within the glass as they experiment. Experienced alchemists have hundreds of such flasks, filled with exotic materials from across the world. Less experienced alchemists are probably dead because they stored their concoctions in a less adequate container.\n\nThis flask is filled with water.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14601_ShortDesc", "A mold used for creating flasks")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14601_LongDesc", "Due to their need for somewhere to store volatile concoctions alchemists are usually proficient in the art of glass creation.\nIt also ensures that if somebody dies due to a flaw in their glasswork releasing a noxious poison into their workshop, they only have themselves to blame.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14999_ShortDesc", "The heart of a worshipper of Hanuman")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14999_LongDesc", "This heart was ripped from the chest of a loyal worshipper of Hanuman.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15001_ShortDesc", "Stolen from a chest somewhere")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15001_LongDesc", "One of the most important facets of the worship of Set is ritual sacrifice. With consecrated blades, the worshippers of Set will cut the hearts from their enemies and offer them as sacrifice on the altar of their demonic god.\nFor the snakes who gather at the dark altars of the serpent god, human hearts provide a rare delicacy.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15002_ShortDesc", "Carefully harvested, this meat is ritually pure.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15002_LongDesc", "This flesh has not known the touch of a blade and is therefore ritually pure in the eyes of the Yog religion.\nThe desert men of Darfar, even those who are enslaved in the great city states that make up the kingdom of Shem, partake of ritually pure human flesh at least once every cycle of the moon.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15003_ShortDesc", "The last lingering presence of the soul")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15003_LongDesc", "Unlike the other religions of the age, worshippers of Mitra favor dignified and elegant rituals. They frown upon human sacrifice and prefer to perform purification rituals upon the dead.\nOstensibly, this ritual involves positioning the Ankh of Mitra over the body of the deceased and saying a few quiet prayers. The ankh is then touched to the corpse, in order to cleanse it of any last impurities.\nSome of the more experienced priests have noticed that at the moment of contant, their ankh becomes slightly heavier, as if something is clinging to the instrument. Those priests are often given vows of silence, shortly thereafter.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15004_ShortDesc", "Blood extracted from a victim")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15004_LongDesc", "This blood, harvested using a ritual tool of Jhebbal Sag, contains something of the ancient past when men and beasts shared a language and hunted by each others side.\n\nThis is the essence of Jhebbal Sag, scattered from his divinity and reclaimed, piece by piece, to be offered up in sacrifice at his altars.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15051_ShortDesc", "XX_Yog Favor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15051_LongDesc", "XX_Yog Favor")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15052_ShortDesc", "XX_Set Favor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15052_LongDesc", "XX_Set Favor")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15053_ShortDesc", "XX_Mitra Favor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15053_LongDesc", "XX_Mitra Favor")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15054_ShortDesc", "XX_Ymir Favor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15054_LongDesc", "XX_Ymir_Favor")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15101_ShortDesc", "XX_Yog Tribute")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15101_LongDesc", "XX_Yog Tribute")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15102_ShortDesc", "XX_Set Tribute")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15102_LongDesc", "XX_Set Tribute")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15501_ShortDesc", "The heart of a fallen hero")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15501_LongDesc", "This heart was taken from the chest of one who once called themselves a hero. The definition shifts between cultures and locations so being sure that one has captured the heart of a hero is a difficult business. Most sorcerers simply content themselves with trying out hundreds of hearts, in the hope that the odds are on their side.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15502_ShortDesc", "The horn of an ancient rhinoceros")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15502_LongDesc", "There is a certain energy in the fall of an ancient beast. This horn, taken from an ancient rhinocerous, is an occult focal point. Who knows to what use such an artefact could be put?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15503_ShortDesc", "An ancient key")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15503_LongDesc", "This key is of Lemurian origins. It looks like it would fit some of the doors in the Black Keep.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15504_ShortDesc", "A heart ripped from the chest of the commander of The Silent Legion.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15504_LongDesc", "The heart is still beating. The dark energies contained within this heart could be used by a skilled enough craftsman.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15505_ShortDesc", "A staff topped with a serpentine skull")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15505_LongDesc", "This staff, found in the acid pit alongside the Abysmal Remnant, is marked with an ancient language. The first runs along the length of the staff in glowing runes, whereas the second is carved rudely over the top of the first script, obscuring pieces of it.

While unintelligible at first glance, beneath the glow of the bracelet, the runes shape themselves into a recognizable script that reads:

"A gift from the ...B... give us advice ...E... and allow us to control the ...T... must be brought ...R... The Tower of the Bat where ...A... placed on the altar ...Y... awakened to share with us ...E... only awakened by ...R... and their blood."

Reading the script is one thing, understanding what it means is something else entirely.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15506_ShortDesc", "A staff topped with a serpentine skull that has glowing eyes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15506_LongDesc", "This staff, awakened during a ritual on top of the Tower of the Bat, seems to be possessed by the spirit of a demon. \n\nWhen called upon, the demon can offer advice to the wielder, but whether it can be trusted is a completely different story.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15507_ShortDesc", "An ornate diadem worn by the Giant-kings")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15507_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Kallian Publico believed that it contained the diadem of the giant-kings, of the people who dwelt in that dark land before the ancestors of the Stygians came there. He showed me a design carved on the lid, which he swore was the shape of the diadem which legend tells us the monster-kings wore.</> - Rogues in the House

Too large to be worn by a human, this diadem hums with contained power. Taken from the Priestking of the Giant-kings - known today as the Barrow King - the story of the diadem is one of betrayal and hatred.

It seems that the Priestking was the father of Tyros the Deathbringer. Tyros turned against his father at some point during the war between the Lemurians and the Giant-kings and his father cursed him, and all of his loyal warriors.

Such is the strength of the diadem, that Tyros and his men were cursed to live forever, a Silent Legion brooding in the ruins of the north.
This is one of the artefacts required to create the keystone that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15508_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by the Witch Queen of Lemuria")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15508_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Many Lemurians escaped to the eastern coast of the Thurian Continent, which was comparatively untouched. There they were enslaved by the ancient race which already dwelt there, and their history, for thousands of years, is a history of brutal servitude.</> - The Hyborian Age

This mask was used by the Witch Queens of Lemuria to communicate with their primary deity, Dagon, before their kingdom sank into the ocean during the cataclysm.

When the Lemurians crossed into the land of the Giant-kings, they negotiated for somewhere to settle. The Witch Queen, weary of the forced exile of her people, helped the Giant-kings to forge the bracelets, originally to facilitate communication between the two races.

Later, this mask possessed the exile Razma, controlling her thoughts and forcing her to start rebuilding the palace at the heart of Xel-ha.
This is one of the artefacts required to create the keystone that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15509_ShortDesc", "A crystalline tear from Tyros the Deathbringer")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15509_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Tears rolled from the sightless eyes, and Conan's gaze strayed to the limbs stretched on the marble couch. And he knew the monster would not rise to attack him. He knew the marks of the rack, and the searing brand of the flame, and tough-souled as he was, he stood aghast at the ruined deformities which his reason told him had once been limbs as comely as his own. And suddenly all fear and repulsion went from him to be replaced by a great pity.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

This single tear, shed by Tyros the Deathbringer, is an object of immense power. Tyros, was the half-blood child of  the Priestking and an unknown human slave. Whether his birth was natural or aided by sorcery, is not known, but it is known that Tyros had children of his own with his wife, Telith.

Tyros was raised a gladiator, fighting in the arena for the benefit of the Giant-kings, but when war broke out with the Lemurians, he became a leader in their armies. Through great feats of strength and will, he won the outpost of Xullan from the Lemurian army. Just south of there, he met Telith, a daughter of Lemuria, and everything changed...

This is one of the artefacts required to create the keystone that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15510_ShortDesc", "A crazy angled stone kept within an alien box")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15510_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It was treasured and placed in its curious box by the crinoid things of Antarctica, salvaged from their ruins by the serpent-men of Valusia... "</> - The Haunter of the Dark, H.P. Lovecraft

This artefact is spoken of in whispers by the nighted cults of the Hyborian age. It is rumored to be a window into all of space and time - but with the cost that the user risks baring their soul to powers from the outer dark.

The Serpentmen of Valusia were in possession of this object, and how they came to be living beneath the volcano in the Exiled Lands is a mystery. Perhaps fleeing their genocide at the hands of the legendary Kull of Atlantis, they made their way to the Exiled Lands where they befriended the Giant-kings through worship of their deity, Set. In return they were allowed to live in the Caldera of the volcano and build their cities there.

It was, however, too late for the serpent men, a degenerate and dying race, lacking the genetic diversity to continue. They found themselves coupling with snakes and lesser reptiles in the hope of preserving their species but as time passed, they lost all hope of survival and instead, preyed for bitter revenge upon the races.

They crafted a staff with their ancient magics and summoned a presence via the trapezohedron, to inhabit the staff and lead the Giant-kings to their downfall.

If they must die, they would take as many with them as possible and most especially, the cursed children of humankind.

This is one of the artefacts required to create the keystone that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15511_ShortDesc", "A gleaming jewel on an ornate pin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15511_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">So you could steal from him the only thing he would never give you -- the ring with the jewel men call the Star of Khorala -- the star stolen from the queen of Ophir, who would pay a roomful of gold for its return. He would not give it to you willingly, because he knew that it holds a magic which, when properly controlled, will enslave the hearts of any of the opposite sex.</> - Shadows in Zamboula

The Star of the Champion is a gem of unsurpassed beauty - glowing with a white light that sets the world to shimmering. 

Once, in the ancient past, it was awarded to Tyros the Deathbringer for becoming the champion of the Giant-kings arena. 

In his final battle, he was to fight the mightiest dragon created by the Giant-kings, a magnificent creature of enormous stature. Tyros defeated the beast, but in his victory, he saw the death of something noble and he wept. He pinned the Star of the Champion to the corpse of the creature - and the mighty beast was buried right there, beneath the sands of the arena.

Later, when Tyros was cursed with immortality, the dragon inherited the curse and rose again to stalk the arena.

This is one of the artefacts required to create the keystone that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15512_ShortDesc", "A stone containing an enslaved elemental ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15512_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He it was who shook down the cliffs at Valkia, by his spells that enthrall the elementals of the earth-he it was who sent the creature of darkness into your tent before dawn.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Also known as the Scourgestone, this unassuming chunk of stone contains the elemental that plagues the Exiled Lands with continual sandstorms.

Enslaved by the Priestking in his desperation to end the war after the Shattering on the Plains, he gave it over to the Warmaker to release at the right moment.

When the time came, the Warmaker shattered the stone into fragments and scattered them across the battlefield, freeing the elemental to do its work.

It seemed to work, gathering a gigantic storm that crossed the Exiled Lands, moving towards the city of Xel-ha in the far east.
But the Giant-kings had not reckoned with the power of the human spirit. A Lemurian priest named Petruso went out to confront the sandstorm. Using the power of Dagon, he anchored the elemental controlling the sandstorm to his flesh, preventing it from moving further east and destroying the Lemurian city.

He saved his people, yes, but Petruso paid a terrible price. His sacrifice had not stopped the sandstorm, it had simply put it into a temporal loop. It passed across the Exiled Lands, time and time again, stopping when it reached Petruso... then starting again.

Eventually this drove him insane.

This is one of the artefacts required to create the keystone that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15513_ShortDesc", "A black essence left by the Servant of the Ring")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15513_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">By Set, mine enemy knew not the hour when he might awake at midnight to feel the taloned fingers of a nameless horror at his throat! I did dark and terrible magic with the Serpent Ring of Set, which I found in a nighted tomb a league beneath the earth, forgotten before the first man crawled out of the slimy sea.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

Thoth Amon of the Black Ring is the man who created the Exiled Lands.

During one of his journeys seeking sorcerous knowledge, he stumbled upon the Unnamed City and, befriending the lone survivor, Warmaker Klael, he soon learned of the powerful artefacts contained beneath the city.

Exploring the ruins, he found the Serpent Ring of Set, and the slave bracelets of the Giant-kings. In his twisted mind, a plan began to form.
A deal was struck with King Cstephon of Stygia. Thoth Amon would provide the bracelets and a place where the political and ideological enemies of the king could be exiled forever (but kept alive as a contingency for the future) and in return, King Cstephon would provide troops to occasionally ride through the Exiled Lands and collect any artefacts that the poor unfortunates had obtained.

This then was the founding of the Exiled Lands and the Purge, though over the years the deal has altered and Thoth Amon has extended his offer to other rulers across the world (without the knowledge of King Cstephon, naturally).

Thoth Amon has moved further and further from the concerns of the  worldly - he no longer deals personally with the affairs of the Exiled Lands. Instead, he sends his enforcer, the Servant of the Ring to deal with any major problems.

This essence, taken from the Servant of the Ring, hopefully contains enough of the dark sorcery to complete the ritual to create the keystone, that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15514_ShortDesc", "A jagged piece of stone that pulses with power")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15514_LongDesc", "This is a piece of the legendary Scourgestone. But it is broken and must be reassembled by one who understands the power that it holds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15515_ShortDesc", "A shattered piece of stone that pulses with power")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15515_LongDesc", "This is a piece of the legendary Scourgestone. But it is broken and must be reassembled by one who understands the power that it holds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15516_ShortDesc", "A broken piece of stone that pulses with power")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15516_LongDesc", "This is a piece of the legendary Scourgestone. But it is broken and must be reassembled by one who understands the power that it holds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15517_ShortDesc", "A keystone that unlocks the bracelet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15517_LongDesc", "This keystone, created through a ritual, contains the essence of the artefacts that were used to create the slave bracelets of the Giant-kings.

It can be used to remove a slave bracelet from one who is exiled. This is an extremely powerful artefact and must be used with caution.
Simply use the item to remove the bracelet.

WARNING: REMOVING THE BRACELET WILL END THE GAME AND DELETE YOUR CHARACTER!")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15518_ShortDesc", "A key to open the door to Razma\'s Quarters")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15518_LongDesc", "This small key opens a door in Sepermeru,  which is where Razma returned after being freed from the Mask of the Witch Queen.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16001_ShortDesc", "A mixture for hardening stone pieces")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16001_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands stand as a testament to the efficacy of weather at destroying the works of man. When the wind howls across the landscape and the sand scours everything in its path, there are few buildings that survive for very long.\nHowever, the supernaturally large insects of the Exiled Lands have developed a natural secretion that helps to protect them against the environment. \nIchor from these creatures, when soaked into twine and bound to a stone surface, can be placed into a furnace and hardened into bricks that provide excellent protection against the rigors of the Exiled Lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16002_ShortDesc", "An iron frame used to reinforce walls.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16002_LongDesc", "The weakness of stone lies in the spaces between the bricks themselves and the materials that bind them together. This reinforcement, crafted of iron, helps to create a solid frame for the stones.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16003_ShortDesc", "A steel frame used to reinforce walls.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16003_LongDesc", "The weakness of stone lies in the spaces between the bricks themselves and the materials that bind them together. This reinforcement, crafted of steel, helps to create a solid frame for the stones.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16011_ShortDesc", "Shaped stones for construction")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16011_LongDesc", "Loose fitting stones are a poor defense against the elements and the creatures of the Exiled Lands. Bricks, cut from sections of sandstone, provide more strength to structures and can be butressed with iron and steel to create sturdy walls and strong defenses.\n\nThese bricks are shaped to fit, but have not undergone any more specific treatment.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16012_ShortDesc", "Shaped, furnace-hardened stones for construction")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16012_LongDesc", "Loose fitting stones are a poor defense against the elements and the creatures of the Exiled Lands. Bricks, cut from sections of sandstone, provide more strength to structures and can be butressed with iron and steel to create sturdy walls and strong defenses.\n\nThese bricks are shaped to fit and have also been treated with a consolidant and steel reinforcement, making anything constructed of them almost impregnable.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16021_ShortDesc", "Shaped wood for construction")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16021_LongDesc", "It is possible to create basic weapons and items from branches collected from the ground, but any flaws in the wood quickly become apparent and such items break quickly.\nShaped wood is harvested wood that has been shaped by the carpenters hand to avoid structural weakness and provide additional resilience.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17001_ShortDesc", "A darkening agent for dyes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17001_LongDesc", "When this dark substance is added to a dye, it darkens it to produce a shade that is darker than the original dye, without changing the color.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17002_ShortDesc", "A lightening agent for dyes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17002_LongDesc", "When this light substance is added to a dye, it lightens it to produce a shade that is lighter than the original dye, without changing the color.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17010_ShortDesc", "A flask of brown dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17010_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")
