column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18000_ShortDesc", "Seed cones of the hop plant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18000_LongDesc", "As the monks of a particular order are fond of saying, \'Beer is proof that Mitra desires us to be happy.\' Hops is the flavoring agent and heart of many of man\'s most loved libations.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18001_ShortDesc", "Yeast used in the baking of bread and fermentation of alcohol.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18001_LongDesc", "Certain yeasts, harvested by any number of means, creates a softer, tastier bread than flatbreads. This yeast, harvested from certain plants, makes a most effective leavening agent.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18002_ShortDesc", "The viscous, sweet bounty of bees")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18002_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'But your skin is white as milk, your eyes are clear as dawn, and there is about you a freshness and daintiness alluring as honey.\'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk\n\nEven at the lowest point in the cycle of savagery and civilization, mankind never fails to value honey. The sweet, viscous food substance miraculously defies contagion and rot. It is used in cooking. The very first fermented beverages came from honey. Medicine men and women know to apply honey to rashes, wounds, and burns - to administer it to ease coughs and sore throats. Honey is even employed in certain Stygian embalming techniques.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18005_ShortDesc", "Small, red berries")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18005_LongDesc", "Growing in the cold of the highlands, these berries are used in the making of juice and wine. They can be eaten, though they do not offer much nourishment. Still, any sustenance is good sustenance when waiting for meatier prey.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18006_ShortDesc", "Small, blue berries")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18006_LongDesc", "Growing in the dry wastes of the desert, these berries are used in the making of juice and wine. They can be eaten, though they do not offer much nourishment. Still, any sustenance is precious out in the desolate lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18007_ShortDesc", "May not be safe to eat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18007_LongDesc", "Mushrooms can be used to enhance an otherwide bland dish. Or poison it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18008_ShortDesc", "A mushroom that violently discharges poisonous spores")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18008_LongDesc", "For a very long time, alchemists ignored the properties of the puffball mushroom in favour of studying the various types of lotus and their effects.\nIn recent times, however, puffball mushrooms have become a popular area of study since they are less deadly and ultimately easier to grow and handle than lotus.\nThese mushrooms can be harvested for their spores, which can be used to fill a glass orbs and dispersed to form a poisonous cloud at the discretion of the wielder.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18010_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from small fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18010_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is harvested from small fish not known for being good eating. It is not particularly filling or flavorful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18011_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18011_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is harvested from fish known for being good eating. It is easy to cook and full of flavor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18012_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from exotic fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18012_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is taken from one of the exotic species of fish swimming in the waters of the Exiled Lands. The effect of this meat is particularly potent, but whether this boost is due to the rare flavour or is an aftereffect of the thrilling catch is a matter for sages to discuss.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18013_ShortDesc", "Preserved fish flesh")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18013_LongDesc", "Salting and drying are among man\'s earliest means of preserving food. This fish flesh will resist decay for a while.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18014_ShortDesc", "Preserved animal flesh")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18014_LongDesc", "Salting and drying are among man\'s earliest means of preserving food. This animal flesh will resist decay for a while.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18015_ShortDesc", "Preserved fish flesh")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18015_LongDesc", "Salting and drying are among man\'s earliest means of preserving food. This fish combo has been dried and spiced to perfection. Despite this dish being quite spicy, it does not warm you in any notable fashion.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18020_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from middling shellfish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18020_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is harvested from shellfish not known for being good eating. It is not particularly filling or flavorful, and the shell-to-meat ratio is not very good.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18021_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from shellfish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18021_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is harvested from shellfish known for being good eating. It is easy to cook and full of flavor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18022_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from exotic shellfish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18022_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is taken from one of the exotic species of crustaceans or molluscs dwelling in the waters of the Exiled Lands. The effect of this meat is particularly potent, but whether this boost is due to the rare flavour or is an aftereffect of the thrilling catch is a matter for sages to discuss.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18025_ShortDesc", "Baked wood ready to burn")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18025_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Among the forest-covered hills of the northwest exist wandering bands of ape-men, without human speech, or the knowledge of fire or the use of implements.</> - The Hyborian Age\n\nFire protected mankind from feral predators and took them one more rung up the ladder of savagery and civilization. Humanity ever looks for ways to build a better fire. These kiln-baked pieces of wood are better fuel for a superior fire.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18029_ShortDesc", "A manuscript written by the Archivist himself")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18029_LongDesc", "This book describes the adventures of a barbarian and his encounter with a dark well, which he is too afraid to jump down into as he hears whispering voices from it. The story feels... wrong. But it is strangely inspiring when read. If written by another author, it could have been a very good read.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18030_ShortDesc", "A syrupy substance bled from trees")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18030_LongDesc", "Known as the blood of trees, particularly of those growing in the highlands. Resin weeps from the wounds cleaved into bark, protecting the plant from injury and illness. Humankind has found some uses for the viscous stuff, including certain perfumes and incenses precious to religious rites.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18031_ShortDesc", "A viscous liquid used for fuel")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18031_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">With one motion he extinguished the lamp and drew his sword.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThis viscous liquid is harvested from plants, animals, and the bowels of the earth itself. It has myriad uses, including fuel for fire. Oil lamps offer a long-lasting flame, taking humanity another rung up the ladder of civilization, combatting the dark that teems with predators.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18032_ShortDesc", "Red berry pulp")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18032_LongDesc", "This red-colored pulp, squeezed from highland berries, can be used to make wine.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18033_ShortDesc", "Blue berry pulp")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18033_LongDesc", "This blue-colored pulp, squeezed from desert berries, can be used to make wine.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18034_ShortDesc", "A manuscript written by the Archivist himself")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18034_LongDesc", "This book describes the life of a pregnant mother who believes her child will grow up to become a witch. Nothing about this story feels right but reading it is strangely inspiring nonetheless. If written by another author, it could have been a very good read.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18035_ShortDesc", "A manuscript written by the Archivist himself")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18035_LongDesc", "This manuscript tells the tale of a tower made out of living elephants and a barbarian that attempts to climb it for no obvious reason. Nothing about this story feels right but reading it is strangely inspiring nonetheless. If written by another author, it could have been a very good read.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18036_ShortDesc", "A manuscript written by the Archivist himself")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18036_LongDesc", "This book describes the life and work-conditions of a barbarian that suffers from fear of blood. Most of the book is dedicated to the barbarian trying to clean his nails. The story feels... wrong. But it is strangely inspiring when read. If written by another author, it could have been a very good read.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18037_ShortDesc", "A manuscript written by the Archivist himself")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18037_LongDesc", "This book tells the story of a prince living on the banks of a river that is polluted by tar from a nearby tannery. Nothing about this story feels right but reading it is strangely inspiring nonetheless. If written by another author, it could have been a very good read.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18038_ShortDesc", "A manuscript written by the Archivist himself")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18038_LongDesc", "This book describes the adventures of one of Ymir\'s daughters, as she learns how to cook food and behead her enemies. It feels familiar, as if the story was stolen from another author and warped, but it is still strangely inspiring. If written by another author, it could have been a very good read.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18039_ShortDesc", "A manuscript written by the Archivist himself")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18039_LongDesc", "This manuscript details the story of a barbarian that gets bitten by a large, scaled lizard and slowly succumbs to its venom. Most of the book is a draw-out study in agony and pain. The story feels... wrong. But it is strangely inspiring when read. If written by another author, it could have been a very good read.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18040_ShortDesc", "Frozen water")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18040_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Soft bellied fools sitting on velvet cushions with naked girls offering them iced wine on their knees...</> - Beyond the Black River\n\nNormally, ice is found only in the frigid north, the highest peaks, or the deep winters. To the people of the Hyborian Age, ice is a rare commodity. Sometimes, the very wealthy are able to acquire the frozen treat, commissioning massive blocks of ice to be brought down from the mountains, so that a tiny speck of it might survive the melting in order to reach their greedy tongues.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18041_ShortDesc", "A cold shard from the Outer Dark")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18041_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">First there was the blackness of an utter void, with the cold winds of cosmic space blowing through it. Then shapes, vague, monstrous and evanescent, rolled in dim panorama through the expanse of nothingness, as if the darkness were taking material form.</> - Queen of the Black Coast\n\nThere exist whole galaxies of dimensions between the spaces of human perception. Substances in the Outer Dark have a material, but not of any composition that follows earthly laws. One of sorcerous intent can, with the proper skills, reach sidewise into the nighted gulfs and pull forth some of these weird substances, such as black ice. This material is cold, the cold from between the stars, a cold that burns. It can be used in the smelting process of star metal.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18050_ShortDesc", "Large, sharp tooth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18050_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The muscles coiling under that gray corpse-like skin were stringy and hard as steel wires, exceeding the strength of a man. But Conan\'s thews were iron too, and his mail saved him from the gnashing fangs and ripping claws long enough for him to drive home his dagger, again and again and again.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThe incisors and large teeth of beasts are often used as adornments by man. Perhaps it is a defiant challenge to the savage world, a reminder that humankind has crawled out of the primordial depths, above the food chain, and their flesh is not for feasting.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18051_ShortDesc", "The horns of a beast")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18051_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'That helmet held the other\'s gaze; it was without a crest, but adorned by short bull\'s horns. No civilized hand ever forged that head-piece.\'</> - Beyond the Black River\n\nThe horns taken from the head of a beast. Horns are used in making jewelry, tools, drinking receptacles, and even instruments of sound.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18052_ShortDesc", "The pelt of a beast")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18052_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Among the furs on the dais was a gorgeous spotted skin, whose predominant hue was golden. It was not a clever copy, but the skin of an actual beast. And that beast, Conan knew, had been extinct for at least a thousand years; it was the great golden leopard which figures so prominently in Hyborian legendry, and which the ancient artists delighted to portray in pigments and marble.</> - The Devil in Iron\n\nPelts, skinned from beasts, with warm or tough or luxuriant fur, are among the earliest materials man has turned to clothing. To wear the skins of creatures the gods left less exposed to the elements - to take on their strength. Furs are prized by both the savage and the civilized.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18053_ShortDesc", "A huge tooth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18053_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Conan stepped out into the nearest square of moonlight, so as to have all the advantage of illumination that he could; for the beast, he knew, could see better than himself in the dark. Instantly the brute saw him; its great yellow tusks gleamed in the shadows, but it made no sound.\'</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nAn oversized, protruding tooth recently ripped from the maw of a beast. Tusks are used in jewelry, tool-making, or simple as a trophy one can carry in their hand.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18054_ShortDesc", "The pelt of a beast")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18054_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Among the furs on the dais was a gorgeous spotted skin, whose predominant hue was golden. It was not a clever copy, but the skin of an actual beast. And that beast, Conan knew, had been extinct for at least a thousand years; it was the great golden leopard which figures so prominently in Hyborian legendry, and which the ancient artists delighted to portray in pigments and marble.</> - The Devil in Iron\n\nPelts, skinned from beasts, with warm or tough or luxuriant fur, are among the earliest materials man has turned to clothing. To wear the skins of creatures the gods left less exposed to the elements - to take on their strength. Furs are prized by both the savage and the civilized.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18060_ShortDesc", "Both stone and metal from the heavens")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18060_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'This is a grisly thing,\' shuddered the clerk. \'It\'s too ancient to be holy. Who ever saw metal like it in a sane world? It seems less destructible than Aquilonian steel, yet see how it is corroded and eaten away in spots.\'</> - The God in the Bowl\n\nThis ore, fallen from the sky, is a gift from the firmament. Put it to your ear and it practically hums with cosmic secrets like the ocean in a seashell.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18061_ShortDesc", "An alloy created from the mysterious star metal ore")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18061_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'All substance is one to him who holds the key of the cosmos\' he said cryptically. \'To an adept nothing is immutable. At will steel blossoms bloom in unnamed gardens, or flower-swords flash in the moonlight.\'</> - The People of the Black Circle\n\nThis fallen metal from the sky, be it a gift from the gods or a curse from the wells of night, has mysterious properties that sages and sorcerers are only beginning to understand. This strange material is not as easy to work with as earthly metals, but those of esoteric skill have devised a way to smelt star metal ore, with a technique that employs brimstone and black ice, to create ingots.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18062_ShortDesc", "Steel ingot of adamantine strength")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18062_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Presently he withdrew the blade and showed her the blue steel stained a dull purplish crimson.</> - Red Nails\n\nThose who know the riddle of steel know how to employ both brimstone and black ice to harden steel bars to a higher quality.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18064_ShortDesc", "A strong, alcoholic beverage")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18064_LongDesc", "Only Vald himself knows what this drink contains but whatever it is it smells of old socks and distilled alcohol.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18065_ShortDesc", "A strong, alcoholic beverage")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18065_LongDesc", "Only Vald himself knows what this drink contains but whatever it is it smells of old socks and distilled alcohol.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18066_ShortDesc", "A strong, alcoholic beverage")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18066_LongDesc", "Only Vald himself knows what this drink contains but whatever it is it smells of old socks and distilled alcohol.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18067_ShortDesc", "A strong, alcoholic beverage")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18067_LongDesc", "Only Vald himself knows what this drink contains but whatever it is it smells of old socks and distilled alcohol.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18068_ShortDesc", "Cures hangovers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18068_LongDesc", "Cures hangovers but also causes a small amount of corruption. Out of the ashes?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18069_ShortDesc", "Written in a very unsteady hand")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18069_LongDesc", "This book contains Vald\'s secret Grog and Rum recipes. Unfortunately, it does not seem to contain the recipe for a hangover cure.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18070_ShortDesc", "Clear, strong drink with an orange tint")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18070_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'They\'re not drunk,\' he muttered presently. \'They\'re not even drinking. What devil\'s game is this?\'</> - The Black Stranger\n\nThe orange phykos, an aquatic plant normally prized for the dyes that can be rendered from it, can also be fermented into a crude sort of rum. Sailors know that phykos rum goes down with a rough burn and leaves the belly warm.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18071_ShortDesc", "Powerful liquor of a mystically green hue")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18071_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He was quick to laugh, quick and terrible in his wrath. He was a valiant trencherman, and strong drink was a passion and a weakness with him.</> - Queen of the Black Coast\n\nA powerful drink, often said to taste like a mixture of dessert and a death god\'s tears, absinthe is often mixed with water and sugar. Poets, artists, and mad revelers of the most decadent disposition swear by this green drink\'s reputed powers to cause visions and reveling bedlam. The Mad King of Ophir, Moranthes II, is said drink the stuff with every meal. Absinthe heavily heats the tongue.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18072_ShortDesc", "A most refreshing beverage")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18072_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">And more than looking the part, he felt the part. The awakening of old memories, the resurge of the wild, mad, glorious days of old before his feet were set on the imperial path when he was a wandering mercenary, roistering, brawling, guzzling, adventuring, with no thought for the morrow, and no desire save sparkling ale, red lips, and a keen sword to swing on all the battlefields of the world.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nOne of the oldest forms of alcoholic drink devised by man. With just enough alcohol to preserve it, ale can save lives when water is tainted or in short supply. It cools and refreshes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18073_ShortDesc", "Wine with a spiced kick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18073_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He remembered great horns of foaming ale, jacks of sparkling wine gulped carelessly or spilled on the tavern floor.</> - A Witch Shall Be Born\n\nIn Vanaheim and in Asgard, it is popular to flavor wine with mulled spices and serve it hot when a fire is available. Such mulled wine heats the body and soul.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18074_ShortDesc", "An unlikely drink, sweeter than expected")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18074_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Give me a clean sword and a clean foe to flesh it in. Damnation! What would I not give for a flagon of wine!</> - The Scarlet Citadel\n\nHumankind will find a way to have its drink, and there are those who learned to make an alcoholic beverage where grapes fear to grow. Made from the fermented juice of the cactus, this wine cools the tongue.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18075_ShortDesc", "Tastes like death, but packs a kick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18075_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">They\'ll be Lying around too drunk to move by this time. If I had a hundred men I could wipe out the whole horde.</> - The Black Stranger\n\nThe term is used for too wide an array of strong drinks, of various qualities, often made from whatever is on hand. With any luck, the drinker will spend the night drunk and not wake up blind. It certainly heats the tongue.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18076_ShortDesc", "Drink made from fermented honey")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18076_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">You laugh greatly, drink deep and bellow good songs; though I never saw another Cimmerian who drank aught but water, or who ever laughed, or ever sang save to chant dismal dirges.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword\n\nMany lands and many people claim the discovery of mead, to be the first to learn that the already wondrous foodstuff of the bee could be fermented into something yet more wondrous. The Aesir and Vanir of Nordheim often seal pacts made in Ymir\'s name with three successive drinks of mead. A sip of this honeyed brew warms the tongue.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18077_ShortDesc", "A dark wine with a burning bouquet")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18077_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Ascalante turned again to his wine. Over the jeweled spires was rising a dawn crimson as blood.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword\n\nThis wine is made using resin, darkening its color. It leaves the drinker feeling warmed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18078_ShortDesc", "Bounty of the grape, drink of the gods")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18078_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Let me live deep while I live; let me know the rich juices of red meat and stinging wine on my palate, the hot embrace of white arms, the mad exultation of battle when the blue blades flame and crimson, and I am content.</> - Queen of the Black Coast\n\nThe alcoholic beverage made from the grape. Different grapes and different techniques in their fermentation produce different vintages. Wine lightly cools the tongue.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18079_ShortDesc", "A very sweet wine")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18079_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">In front of him stood Tsotha, and on divans lounged Strabonus and Amalrus in their silks and gold, gleaming with jewels, naked slave-boys beside them pouring wine into cups carved of a single sapphire.</> - The Scarlet Citadel\n\nA technique out of Arogs uses honey in the processes of fermenting the pulped grapes, producing a wine that is both sweet and medicinal. This is indeed a drink that blesses one\'s health.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18080_ShortDesc", "A particularly thirst-quenching wine")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18080_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Wine!\' gasped the king from the couch where they had laid him. They put a goblet to his bloody lips and he drank like a man half dead of thirst.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword\n\nA light-colored wine, popular in Turan, known to ease a throat that has taken in the dust of the desert roads. It cools the tongue more than the average vintage.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18081_ShortDesc", "Smells kind of funny, but tastes ok")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18081_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The dullest was struck by the contrast between the harsh, taciturn, gloomy commander, and the pirate whose laugh was gusty and ready, who roared ribald songs in a dozen languages, guzzled ale like a toper, and - apparently - had no thought for the morrow.</> - The Pool of the Black One\n\nThere are those who like to put a little something extra in their drink. This beer adds particular strains of mushrooms to the brewing process. Some claim they receive visions in the night after such a draught, but these may just be the dreams of the drunk. This beer heats the tongue.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18188_ShortDesc", "A bizarre gland that can be used to make explosives")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18188_LongDesc", "Harvested from the corpse of a degenerate, imp-like creature found in the Exiled Lands, this gland is a key component for making demon-fire orbs.\nThe mechanism by which these creatures cause themselves to explode is not well understood, though scholars in other lands have reported similar incidents with frogs and ants. \nMost, however, simple agree that the explosions are sorcerous in nature and leave it at that.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18199_ShortDesc", "Cooked strips of fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18199_LongDesc", "Both the savage and the civilized mouth water when strips of meat sizzle and hiss on the skewer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18200_ShortDesc", "Steaming bowl of fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18200_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">It takes an Argossean merchant to wring wealth out of a little waterfront shop that stank of rotten fish and cheap wine.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThe bounty of the rivers and seas are a major food source for many peoples in Hyboria. Such fare may be prepared by roasting, boiling, and many other methods besides.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18201_ShortDesc", "Steaming bowl of fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18201_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">It takes an Argossean merchant to wring wealth out of a little waterfront shop that stank of rotten fish and cheap wine.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThe bounty of the rivers and seas are a major food source for many peoples in Hyboria. Such fare may be prepared by roasting, boiling, and many other methods besides.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18202_ShortDesc", "Steaming bowl of fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18202_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">It takes an Argossean merchant to wring wealth out of a little waterfront shop that stank of rotten fish and cheap wine.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThe bounty of the rivers and seas are a major food source for many peoples in Hyboria. Such fare may be prepared by roasting, boiling, and many other methods besides.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18203_ShortDesc", "An assortment of shellfish, hot and prepared")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18203_LongDesc", "Shellfish comprise a large category of varied and tasty fare. Such meaty bounty can be plucked right from the waters, but cooking reduces the risk of sickness.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18204_ShortDesc", "An assortment of shellfish, hot and prepared")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18204_LongDesc", "Shellfish comprise a large category of varied and tasty fare. Such meaty bounty can be plucked right from the waters, but cooking reduces the risk of sickness.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18205_ShortDesc", "An assortment of shellfish, hot and prepared")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18205_LongDesc", "Shellfish comprise a large category of varied and tasty fare. Such meaty bounty can be plucked right from the waters, but cooking reduces the risk of sickness.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18206_ShortDesc", "A loaf of bread")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18206_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">She gave into his hands a wooden dish heaped with dried  fruits, cheese and barley bread, and a great pot of the heady upland beer, brewed from barley grown in the high valleys.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nBread takes on many forms, baked from various mixtures of dough and water. On the climb from savagery, bread tends to come at the dawn of agriculture.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18207_ShortDesc", "A decadent display of choice meats")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18207_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">His life was a series of feasts and wild debauches. He filled his palace with the fairest girls of the kingdom, willing or unwilling. He blasphemed the gods and sprawled drunken on the floor of the banquet hall wearing the golden crown, and staining his royal purple robes with the wine he spilled.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nSome eat merely to survive another savage day. Others, of a sensual bent, create magnificent feasts of the most exotic meats, feasts that would make the gods salivate unto a deluge. Decadence to the point of madness? Perhaps. But there is something to be said for the great boon of health this grants the eater.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18208_ShortDesc", "Heaps and heaps of glorious meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18208_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Wolves prowled openly along the grass-grown highways, and bands of gaunt, masterless men slunk through the forests. Only in Tarantia was feasting and wealth and pageantry.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nLarge game, in quantity, make for a meal that would put an army of bellies glad. Such a meal offers good health to the eater.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18209_ShortDesc", "Omelette filled with delicious muscles")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18209_LongDesc", "A tasty combination of food from the land and the sea.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18210_ShortDesc", "Dark green egg smelling of ammonia")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18210_LongDesc", "There is a method of preserving eggs, developed in faraway Khitai. The details vary among the people, but this method often involves clay or ash or salt or quicklime. The egg, so preserved, turns to a dark green. Those foreign to the practice often only eat such an egg out of desperation or a drunken dare. There is the chance that the one who preserved it did not use the ancient method precisely. An imperfectly preserved egg might bring terrible sickness to the eater.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18211_ShortDesc", "Crystal-clear water")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18211_LongDesc", "Water is necessary for life, yet it is not always pure. One can risk sickness by drinking from a strange water source. Humankind has learned different methods of purifying their water, from charcoal to boiling.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18212_ShortDesc", "A ritualistic meal in honor of Yog")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18212_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">There were grisly feasts beneath the moon, across whose red disk a bat-like shadow incessantly swept.</> - Queen of the Black Coast\n\nThis feast is consumed in the name of Yog. Yog, the Lorde of Empty Abodes! Yog, cousin of them that slither in the immaculate slime of the Elder Night! All good and fearing worshipers of Yog must dedicate themselves to the consumption of only meat. All the faithful of Yog must taste human flesh once a month, lest they become unclean until they again perform this communion of body and blood.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18213_ShortDesc", "Mounds of cooked, feral meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18213_LongDesc", "A feast of various gamey meats. What such a meal lacks in quality, it makes up for quantity. Gorging on such fare can satisfy the belly and offer a little relief to the injured.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18214_ShortDesc", "Strips of feral meat dried and salted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18214_LongDesc", "Meat can be preserved for a time by salting and drying. The process also improves the flavor, or perhaps covers it up, of stringy and gamy meat. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18215_ShortDesc", "A foreboding liquid of acrid yet sweet aroma")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18215_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Even the arts you call sorcery are governed by cosmic laws.</> - The People of the Black Circle\n\nFoul ingredients are brewed together to make this forbidden drink which corrupts body and soul. Sorcerers covet this libation, for they know that it nourishes a certain, long atrophied organ of the human soul, stimulating it to open like a nocturnal flower and become sensitive to the vibrations and blasphemies of the Outer Dark.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18216_ShortDesc", "Gruel with a dash of flavor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18216_LongDesc", "Spices, ingredients, and oddities often get thrown into gruel to mask the fact that all one has to eat is gruel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18217_ShortDesc", "A zesty haunch of exotic meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18217_LongDesc", "There are clubs and cliques among the elite nobles of Zingara that pride themselves on devouring exotic fare. The rarest of meals. There are rumors such organizations employ warlocks simply to summon otherworldly horrors, just so the dinner guests may dine on its spectral flesh. Whatever the truth, they do enjoy spicing their meats until they pleasantly heat the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18218_ShortDesc", "A ritualistic meal in honor of Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18218_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Their ghastly feasts were considered a sacrifice to the scaly god.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThis feast is consumed in the name of Set. Set, the Old Serpent! Set. Archenemy Iblis! Set, who is known as Damballah in the Southern kingdoms, whose holy scales blind all with their bright darkness! Set is a jealous god and requires constant sacrifices from his chosen. This meal is devoured as an offering to the Lord of Snakes. May it grow a nest of serpents in the belly of the eater.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18219_ShortDesc", "Cooked and zesty oysters")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18219_LongDesc", "Any Zingaran buccaneer will swear to a very specific regimen before a night of passionate romance:  to devour a dozen spiced oysters in quick succession. This seafood heats the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18220_ShortDesc", "Oysters served hot")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18220_LongDesc", "The fruit of the shell, the bounty of the sea, cooked and safe for consumption. Oysters have a way of becoming a delicacy to most any culture that rests on the water\'s edge.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18221_ShortDesc", "Sweet drink made from berries")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18221_LongDesc", "This drink, made from squeezed berries, is sweet to the taste and lightly cools the parched tongue.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18222_ShortDesc", "A ritualistic meal in honor of Mitra")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18222_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Mitra grant that I do not fail of this mighty trust!</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThis feast is consumed in the name of Mitra. Mitra, chief god of Hyboria! Mitra, the righteous, the father of justice, the enemy of Set! May this meal open a holy and eternal spring in the belly.  May man\'s heart know mercy. Mitra, guard us against the powers of darkness.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18223_ShortDesc", "Various meat scraps cooked together")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18223_LongDesc", "Waste not, want not. When a variety of meat scraps accrue, it is prudent to gather them and cook them all together before they spoil.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18224_ShortDesc", "A hearty bowl of broth and other bits of food")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18224_LongDesc", "When one has a fresh bone and water and a few other odds and ends left over, they have enough to make a satisfying soup.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18225_ShortDesc", "It is gruel, but it actually smells good")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18225_LongDesc", "Sometimes one is able to find a few extra things to throw into the gruel, to make it a more satisfying meal.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18226_ShortDesc", "Smells sharp")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18226_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">It is not against men I must shield you. There are dark worlds barely guessed by man, wherein formless monsters stalk - fiends which may be drawn from the Outer Voids to take material shape and rend and devour at the bidding of evil magicians.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword\n\nIt is said that the long-dead sage Epemitreus devised a modest brew, by steeping a very particular mix of herbs and ingredients in boiling water, that could cleanse a small amount of the corrupting influence of the Outer Dark from one\'s mind and body.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18227_ShortDesc", "A zesty brew")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18227_LongDesc", "Strong tea, steeped with potent spices, can drastically refresh one\'s stamina while heating the body and mind. Turanian guards who draw the late shift are said to be quite fond of this drink on cold, desert nights.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18228_ShortDesc", "A medicinal brew")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18228_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He was a magician from far Khitai, returning to his native kingdom after a journey to Stygia. He took me with him to purple-towered Paikang, its minarets rising amid the vine-festooned jungles of bamboo, and there I grew to womanhood under his teaching.</> - A Witch Shall Be Born\n\nThis brew, a recipe from far away Khitai, revitalizes one\'s stamina in small measures, and moderately heals the wary and injured over time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18229_ShortDesc", "Strips of exotic meat dried and salted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18229_LongDesc", "There are those who say drying and salting such fare is a waste of superior meat, but there are also those who want a finer sort of dry ration to reach into their bag for on faraway and lonely trails.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18230_ShortDesc", "Slice of meat and sizzling eggs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18230_LongDesc", "When one can spare a cut of succulent meat, a breakfast of eggs becomes a heartier meal that makes the heart happy and the belly more than full.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18231_ShortDesc", "Zesty slab of succulent meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18231_LongDesc", "There are those who like the natural taste of the meat, cooked rare so that one\'s teeth still draw blood. And there are those who prefer to inundate their meat with all manner of spices. This dish heats the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18232_ShortDesc", "Strips of succulent meat dried and salted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18232_LongDesc", "Many a hungry soul, when seeing a fine cut of meat from large game, desire to devour it all in one sitting. The wiser sort know when to ration off a bit and salt and dry it for hungrier nights ahead.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18233_ShortDesc", "Cooked strips of succulent meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18233_LongDesc", "Both the savage and the civilized mouth water when strips of meat sizzle and hiss on the skewer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18234_ShortDesc", "Full of things with no legs or too many legs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18234_LongDesc", "The tribes of Darfar know how to find hidden sustenance. Certain grubs and meaty insects, combined with certain herbs, make for a surprisingly refreshing soup. Served cold, this dish moderately cools the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18235_ShortDesc", "A zesty soup")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18235_LongDesc", "Zingarans are known for making a spicy soup that puts a little fire in one\'s belly, heating the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18236_ShortDesc", "A green soup with no meat at all")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18236_LongDesc", "Many a survivor knows to apply the juice of the aloe to a burn or to seek the plant\'s moisture when trekking out in the hot wastes, but certain crones and culinary masters know the healing properties of cooking aloe in a soup. Such a meal offers seemingly instant and moderate relief to the injured.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18237_ShortDesc", "A soup of boiled seeds")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18237_LongDesc", "The bounty of plants are many, and a surplus of seeds can be turned into a filling soup.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18238_ShortDesc", "Soup boiled from that infamous blossom")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18238_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He halted at an ebony door, in the center of which was a grinning silver skull, and pushed it open. He looked into a chamber of ebony and jet, and saw, on a black silken couch, a tall, spare form reclining. Yara the priest and sorcerer lay before him, his eyes open and dilated with the fumes of the yellow lotus, far-staring, as if fixed on gulfs and nighted abysses beyond human ken.</> - The Tower of the Elephant\n\nWhile the yellow lotus can make a mind forget its past, one may cook it into a soup and boil out this property. So prepared, it becomes a safe and rather mundane meal, despite the mystical mystique surrounding the flower.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18239_ShortDesc", "A stew floating with mushrooms")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18239_LongDesc", "A surplus of mushrooms can make a surprisingly hearty stew.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18240_ShortDesc", "Bowlful of cooked mushrooms")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18240_LongDesc", "Some mushrooms are poisonous, it is true, but many can be cooked into a culinary delight. Properly prepared, roasted mushrooms are good for the eater\'s health over time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18241_ShortDesc", "Hot and smelling of winter spices")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18241_LongDesc", "This special brew, heated and loaded with mulled spices, heavily warms a soul even on the longest of winter nights.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18242_ShortDesc", "It\'s hot, and its filling")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18242_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'They have no hope here or hereafter,\' answered Conan. \'Their gods are Crom and his dark race, who rule over a sunless place of everlasting mist, which is the world of the dead. Mitra! The ways of the Aesir were more to my liking.\'</> - The Phoenix on the Sword\n\nThe Cimmerians are a hearty people, and they make their meals equally hearty when they can afford to. But Cimmerians are also a grim people, and things such as spice and flavor rarely touch their tongues.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18243_ShortDesc", "Shroom tea with a zesty kick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18243_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The full lips opened and spoke a single word, in a rich vibrant tone that was like the golden chimes that ring in the jungle-lost temples of Khitai.</> - The God in the Bowl\n\nThe mystics of jungle-cradled Khitai know of certain fungi to brew in their tea, for the purposes of expanding their consciousness to fathom realms both resplendently bright and dark as the nighted voids.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18244_ShortDesc", "Chunks of succulent meat floating in a stew")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18244_LongDesc", "Meat chopped up and cooked in a broth of vegetables makes for a simmering stew that smells both inviting and filling.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18245_ShortDesc", "Links of blackened meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18245_LongDesc", "The blood and flesh of demons are not only components to the profane rituals of sorcerers... but also the culinary arts of the adventurous. These links of cooked meat seem to pulse with eldritch life and eating such fare bestows strong recuperative powers, over time, to the eater.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18246_ShortDesc", "Soup from a great beast\'s head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18246_LongDesc", "There is a very specialized school of divination magic that suggests the future can be divined in a broiled rhinoceros head. There are also hunters who swear the powder of a rhino horn will imbue a man with virility. The veracity of these claims is highly suspect. What is known is that a soup, boiled from the head of a rhino, will imbue the eater with greater power to carry a heavy load.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18247_ShortDesc", "A heavy and fatty meal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18247_LongDesc", "A meal heavy with fat will stay in one\'s stomach, and keep them well fed for some time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18248_ShortDesc", "Zesty meat wrapped in crocodile skin")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18248_LongDesc", "It is said that pirates from the Black Coast created this delicacy by wrapping strips of meat in crocodile skin, heavily spicing the concoction, and then cooking it all until it is crackling crisp. This dish heats one\'s pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18249_ShortDesc", "Chunks of exotic meat floating in a fine stew")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18249_LongDesc", "Only the choicest cuts of meat go into this superior stew.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18250_ShortDesc", "Meaty and eye-wateringly spiced")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18250_LongDesc", "A specialty of desert caravans. Whatever meat is available is mixed and stewed and livened with copious amounts of spice. This dish will heavily heat the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18251_ShortDesc", "A meal both filling and flavorful")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18251_LongDesc", "Only the heartiest meals can prepare one for the savage world.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18252_ShortDesc", "Under the delicious broth is something that was recently...human")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18252_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Yet what creature but man breaks bones for their marrow? Perhaps those remnants were mute evidence of a horrible, cannibalistic feast...</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nA delicacy out of Darfar. The proper way to serve this delicious, hot broth is with a hull human skull in the bowl, slowly revealed with every slurping spoonful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18253_ShortDesc", "Zesty scraps of feral meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18253_LongDesc", "One of the best uses for strong spice is to improve the flavor of gamey meat, shredded to make up for this chewy toughness. Tavern owners share a proverb: \'A dead rat and a jar of spice will get you a lot further in life than just a dead rat.\' This dish heats the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18254_ShortDesc", "Roasted bugs on a skewer")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18254_LongDesc", "A trick learned from the people of Kush is to skewer assortments of large insects and grubs, with bits of vegetable or fruit for flavor, and roast it all on a fire. It makes for a surprisingly tasty treat.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18255_ShortDesc", "Zesty cooked eggs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18255_LongDesc", "Eggs can be livened up with the right spices. This dish warms the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18256_ShortDesc", "A delicious looking egg...")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18256_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">From the deep gash flowed a strange ichor, and Khosatral cried out like the dirging of a great bell.</> - The Devil in Iron\n\nThese innocent-looking eggs hide a gleeful treachery. Within the obfuscation of the shell there resides a blasphemous gush of ichor. Some sadistic nobles relish springing such a surprise on their guests, savoring the looks on their masticating faces.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18257_ShortDesc", "Eggs sizzling hot")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18257_LongDesc", "Eggs make for a fine, storable food, given by nature in their own containers. Cracked open, eggs cook quickly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18258_ShortDesc", "A handful of dried berries")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18258_LongDesc", "These berries have been dried to preserve them. They do not offer much nourishment, but will resist decay for a time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18259_ShortDesc", "A small snack both savory and sweet")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18259_LongDesc", "A common food practice in Turan is to mix salt with certain sweet fruits. This snack, of salted berries, is both tasty and a little better preserved.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18260_ShortDesc", "A ritualistic meal in honor of Ymir")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18260_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Tall and fair and blue-eyed. Their god is Ymir, the frost-giant, and each tribe has its own king. They are wayward and fierce. They fight all day and drink ale and roar their wild songs all night.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword\n\nThis feast is consumed in the name of Ymir. Ymir, the Frost Giant and father of all lesser giants! Ymir, Lord of Storm and War! May he grant the strength to fight all of the day and drink all of the night. May this meal grant a warrior the bravery to die in battle, earning a place in Ymir\'s hall in Valhalla to feast and revel until the end of days.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18261_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from an oyster")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18261_LongDesc", "This flesh is harvested from an oyster. It is known as a delicacy in many places, and rumored to increase virility.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18262_ShortDesc", "A small turtle, full of delicious potential")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18262_LongDesc", "A small turtle heavy with fat that will stay in one\'s stomach and keep them well fed for some time. Quite cute as well.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18263_ShortDesc", "White, crystalline granules")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18263_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Nay, my men are sick to stretch their legs ashore, and nigh to scurvy from chewing salt pork.</> - The Black Stranger\n\nCivilization pivots around salt, communities forming, like growths, around sources of the stuff. Salt is mined, and it is boiled from salt-laden water. It flavors food. Sometimes, it serves as a form of currency. Perhaps most importantly, salt is the best known food preserver, especially for meat.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18264_ShortDesc", "Powdered, exotic flavors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18264_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Some vagrant scent of spice or palm woke clear-etched images of strange coasts where mangroves grew and drums thundered, of ships locked in battle and decks running blood, of smoke and flame and the crying of slaughter...</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nTaken from the seeds, fruit, roots, and bark of plants, spices are used in cooking, medicine, and the arcane arts. These potent flavors hailed from the east, from Turan, Vendhya, and far away Khitai. The insatiable desire of Stygians to procure spices for their mummification rituals expanded trade along the continent. Flavoring one\'s food with spice warms the soul for a time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18268_ShortDesc", "Zesty scraps of feral meat, drenched in honey")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18268_LongDesc", "One of the best uses for strong spice is to improve the flavor of gamey meat, shredded to make up for this chewy toughness. Tavern owners share a proverb: \'A dead rat and a jar of spice will get you a lot further in life than just a dead rat.\' This dish heats the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18269_ShortDesc", "Eggs sizzling hot with a light covering of honey")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18269_LongDesc", "Eggs make for a fine, storable food, given by nature in their own containers. Cracked open, eggs cook quickly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18270_ShortDesc", "Under the delicious broth is something that was recently...human")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18270_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Yet what creature but man breaks bones for their marrow? Perhaps those remnants were mute evidence of a horrible, cannibalistic feast...</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nA delicacy out of Darfar. The proper way to serve this delicious, hot broth is with a hull human skull in the bowl, slowly revealed with every slurping spoonful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18271_ShortDesc", "It is gruel, but it actually smells good")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18271_LongDesc", "Sometimes one is able to find a few extra things to throw into the gruel, to make it a more satisfying meal.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18272_ShortDesc", "Strips of exotic meat dried, salted and drenched in honey")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18272_LongDesc", "There are those who say drying and salting such fare is a waste of superior meat, but there are also those who want a finer sort of dry ration to reach into their bag for on faraway and lonely trails.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18273_ShortDesc", "A loaf of bread that smells of honey")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18273_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">She gave into his hands a wooden dish heaped with dried  fruits, cheese and barley bread, and a great pot of the heady upland beer, brewed from barley grown in the high valleys.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nBread takes on many forms, baked from various mixtures of dough and water. On the climb from savagery, bread tends to come at the dawn of agriculture.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18274_ShortDesc", "A medicinal brew that smells of honey")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18274_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He was a magician from far Khitai, returning to his native kingdom after a journey to Stygia. He took me with him to purple-towered Paikang, its minarets rising amid the vine-festooned jungles of bamboo, and there I grew to womanhood under his teaching.</> - A Witch Shall Be Born\n\nThis brew, a recipe from far away Khitai, revitalizes one\'s stamina in small measures, and moderately heals the wary and injured over time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18275_ShortDesc", "Bigger is always better no matter what they say")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18275_LongDesc", "Some tinctures are useful. Others are merely... engorging.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18276_ShortDesc", "Links of meat held together by innards. Tasty.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18276_LongDesc", "Loved by some, hated by most - blood sausages are a staple food amongst the tribes of the frozen north. Every part of the animal is used, even the blood that courses through their veins.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18277_ShortDesc", "Delicious!")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18277_LongDesc", "A meal heavy with fat will stay in one\'s stomach, and keep them well fed for some time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18278_ShortDesc", "Scraps of wild boar flesh")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18278_LongDesc", "A meal heavy with fat will stay in one\'s stomach, and keep them well fed for some time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18279_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from a wild boar")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18279_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18280_ShortDesc", "A calorie-filled dinner")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18280_LongDesc", "Only the heartiest meals can prepare one for the savage world.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18281_ShortDesc", "Chunks of succulent meat floating in a stew")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18281_LongDesc", "Meat chopped up and cooked in a broth of vegetables makes for a simmering stew that smells both inviting and filling.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18282_ShortDesc", "Cooked strips of succulent meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18282_LongDesc", "Waste not, want not. When a variety of meat scraps accrue, it is prudent to gather them and cook them all together before they spoil.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18283_ShortDesc", "Salt and fat in a succulent combination")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18283_LongDesc", "A meal heavy with fat will stay in one\'s stomach, and keep them well fed for some time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18284_ShortDesc", "Zesty slab of succulent meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18284_LongDesc", "There are those who like the natural taste of the meat, cooked rare so that one\'s teeth still draw blood. And there are those who prefer to inundate their meat with all manner of spices. This dish heats the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18285_ShortDesc", "A cooked haunch of exquisite meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18285_LongDesc", "A cooked haunch of the best meat these lands have to offer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18286_ShortDesc", "A choice cut")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18286_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18287_ShortDesc", "A salted piece of meat with perfect texture")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18287_LongDesc", "Salted to perfection, this meat will last.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18288_ShortDesc", "A spiced piece of meat with perfect texture")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18288_LongDesc", "There are those who like the natural taste of the meat, cooked rare so that one\'s teeth still draw blood. And there are those who prefer to inundate their meat with all manner of spices. This dish heats the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18289_ShortDesc", "A concoction that temporarily increases accuracy")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18289_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.\n\nThis elixir seems to give a boost to eyesight, useful for archers.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18290_ShortDesc", "A concoction that temporarily increases agility")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18290_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.\n\nThe imbiber of this elixir becomes more graceful, seemingly able to dance among the attacks of their enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18291_ShortDesc", "Brewed from the deadly petals of the black lotus")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18291_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The next instant, with appalling suddenness, the jungle waved and dimmed out before his eyes; he did not hear the screams that burst out awfully not far away, as his knees collapsed, letting him pitch limply to the earth. Above his prostrate form the great black blossoms nodded in the windless air.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

The black lotus is a much feared, oft-discussed, plant. It is said that the scent of the flowers brings mad, blighted dreams that trouble all but the blackest of souls. The juice of the black lotus is death, an instant plunge into darkness from which one can never recover.

It is rumored that the sorcerers of the Black Ring use the Black lotus to recover their necromantic powers. 

This potion, steeped in dark mystery, is death to the unprepared. But for those who know when and how to drink it, it can provide an instant surge of sorcerous power.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18292_ShortDesc", "A concoction that increases encumbrance")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18292_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.\n\nThis elixir is often given to slaves to numb their senses to the heavy loads that their masters pile upon them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18293_ShortDesc", "Brewed from golden lotus petals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18293_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was no dagger in her fingers; they grasped a stalk of golden lotus, the crushed blossoms drooping on the bruised stem.</> - People of the Black Circle

Known for its healing properties, golden lotus has been rumored to be able to mend broken bones, heal scars and even unnaturally extend the life of those who drink it.

This potion will provide a significant healing boost to any who drink it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18294_ShortDesc", "Brewed from the gray lotus plant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18294_LongDesc", "The Grey Lotus plant is rumored to grow only in the swamps of the dead, beyond the land of Khitai. A powder made from these plants is known to drive men into a berserker rage, giving them inhuman strength and brutality - and no capacity for mercy.\n\nThis potion offers a slightly less potent version of the powder - imbibing it will fill a person with battle rage that lends them power and aggression, but they will tire quickly in the midst of battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18295_ShortDesc", "A concoction that increases grit")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18295_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.\n\nThis elixir fills the imbiber with unflinching optimism. This means that they become absolutely certain that they can succeed in their endeavor and they will endure anything to get their task done. Which is useful - right up until they pass out from exhaustion.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18296_ShortDesc", "A potion of squeezed purple lotus juice")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18296_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It is steeped in the juice of the purple lotus which grows in the ghost-haunted swamps of southern Stygia, said the magician.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

The purple lotus plant, which grows in the southern swamps of Stygia, is a favorite weapon of sorcerers. The juice of the plant causes a temporary paralysis - a seemingly sorcerous effect that does not require the actual use of sorcery.

One wonders at the purpose of such a potion, because if all stories are to be believed, the juice of the purple lotus causes temporary paralysis. Why anyone would imbibe it willingly is unknown.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18297_ShortDesc", "A concoction that increases strength")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18297_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.\n\nThis elixir allows an imbiber to push their muscles beyond their normal limits. For a limited period of time, they can perform feats of immense strength proportionate to their original strength, of course. It is said that Zamorian street performers drink this potion to increase their strength during performances.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18298_ShortDesc", "A concoction that increases survivability")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18298_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.

This elixir seems to have a digestive effect on the drinker, allowing them to quickly process foods and other concoctions taken through the mouth.

Ironically, perhaps, this elixir is most often taken by apothecaries (or their servants) when they are about to test a new concoction.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18299_ShortDesc", "A concoction that increases vitality")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18299_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.\n\nThis elixir provides the drinker with a feeling of robust health. Wounds seem to matter less under the influence of this potion, which is either a blessing or a curse depending on the scenario.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18300_ShortDesc", "A potion brewed from the frost lotus")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18300_LongDesc", "Unlike the other flowers of this family, the frost lotus has no towering reputation for strange mystical effects. It is possible that alchemists have simply not discovered the best possible use of this blossom - further experimentation is the only way to find out.\nDrinking this potion will definitely have some effect. It\'s just that nobody is sure what it is.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18301_ShortDesc", "A potion that increases underwater breathing time")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18301_LongDesc", "This potion, made from gently glowing plants, allows the imbiber to spend more time underwater. None are truly sure of how the mechanism works, but it is well known to bandits in Kush, who chew a paste made of the same plants before lying in ambush beneath the waters of rivers that run beside major trade routes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18302_ShortDesc", "A ritualistic meal in honor of Jhebbal Sag")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18302_LongDesc", "In honor of the god who hunts, lord of beasts and claws and fangs, this meal is prepared to sate even the most hungry predator.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18303_ShortDesc", "A holy food served at the orgies of Derketo")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18303_LongDesc", "The rituals of Derketo are often mocked by outsiders who do not understand the pleasures and lusts of the goddess. This feast, however, typifies the food served at the revels and orgies of the goddess. No rich or fatty foods here, no. This meal is designed to titillate and preserve the participants, awakening the tingling warmth of the goddess inside them and giving them the stamina to proceed through the night. \n\nOnly untutored fools think that the men and women who laze around the gauzy temples of Derketo are recovering from a night of strong wine.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18304_ShortDesc", "A concoction that frees the imbiber ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18304_LongDesc", "The priests and priestesses of Derketo have often had to deal with penitents who were too reserved or too unwilling to participate in the orgiastic ceremonies of the goddess.\n\nThis potion adds a spring to their step while freeing their mind of any... moral impediments. The practical effect is that any who drink this cannot be stopped, by physical or mental means.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18305_ShortDesc", "A concoction that temporarily increases accuracy")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18305_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.\n\nThis elixir seems to give a boost to eyesight, useful for archers.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18306_ShortDesc", "A lure intended to draw a demonic creatures")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18306_LongDesc", "A bundle of urine-soaked hides and foul-smelling meats bound in lengths of twine. While the ingredients were chosen specifically to appeal to demons, they are nauseating to a human.\n\nThis can be placed on the ground to attract the attention of nearby beasts.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18320_ShortDesc", "A potion that gives the ability to breathe underwater")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18320_LongDesc", "This potion, made from crushed scales, allows the imbiber to breathe underwater for a prolongued period of time. The potion is sickeningly sweet and smells like rotting fish, but is effective.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18322_ShortDesc", "A symbol sacred to Jhebbal Sag")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18322_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan turned, squatted and with his knife began scratching a curious symbol in the mold. Stooping to look at it over his shoulder, Balthus felt a crawling of the flesh along his spine, he knew not why. He felt no wind against his face, but there was a rustling of leaves above them and a weird moaning swept ghostily through the branches. Conan glanced up inscrutably, then rose and stood staring somberly down at the symbol he had drawn.</> - Beyond the Black River

Jhebbal Sag was once worshipped by all living things. Though time has dimmed the memory of the Lord of Beasts, still there are animals and men who remember.

This symbol, placed upon the earth, has power. Normal animals will shy away from it - some primal element within them recognizing an ancient language that they have forgotten.

Those who cross it will become a cursed - and a test will begin. In the realm of the beasts, weakness is punished with death and strength is rewarded.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18350_ShortDesc", "A surprisingly smooth drink")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18350_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">In front of him stood Tsotha, and on divans lounged Strabonus and Amalrus in their silks and gold, gleaming with jewels, naked slave-boys beside them pouring wine into cups carved of a single sapphire.</> - The Scarlet Citadel\n\nA technique out of Arogs uses honey in the processes of fermenting the pulped grapes, producing a drink that is both sweet and medicinal. This is indeed a drink that blesses one\'s health. This has since been modified by brewers to a more alcoholic drink that also warms the body.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18351_ShortDesc", "Makes you grow hairs on the hairs that are already on your chest")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18351_LongDesc", "Also makes you grow hair on your palms, feet and tongue. Not particularly tasty, but it certainly warms you up.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18352_ShortDesc", "Incites rage and lowers inhibitions")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18352_LongDesc", "This has been called the nectar of the gods by many a Vanir berserker. It is far more often referred to as \'a good reason to not visit Vanaheim\', second only to the natives themselves.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18353_ShortDesc", "A bitter tea that increases stamina")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18353_LongDesc", "Strong tea, steeped with potent spices, can drastically refresh one\'s stamina while heating the body and mind. Turanian guards who draw the late shift are said to be quite fond of this drink on cold, desert nights.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18354_ShortDesc", "Tastes of venom")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18354_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Wine!\' gasped the king from the couch where they had laid him. They put a goblet to his bloody lips and he drank like a man half dead of thirst.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword\n\nA dark-colored wine, popular in Stygia, known to ease a throat that has taken in the dust of the desert roads. It cools the tongue more than the average vintage. It contains a venom-gland at the bottom of the bottle - purists say that in order to properly drink this, ones lips must touch the gland.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18399_ShortDesc", "Bandages used for binding wounds")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18399_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'She sat on a couch with her wounded leg extended upon it, and the Tecuhltli woman had just bound it with silk bandages. Valeria\'s red-stained sword lay on the couch beside her.\'</> - Red Nails\n\nWounds require special care, to heal and to avoid infection and putrefaction. Sometimes, upon the battlefield, all one can do is bind a wound with strips of fiber.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18400_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'She sat on a couch with her wounded leg extended upon it, and the Tecuhltli woman had just bound it with silk bandages.
