column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80974_ShortDesc", "A place of sacrifice to Ymir, the Frost Giant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80974_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The clangor of the swords had died away, the shouting of the slaughter was hushed; silence lay on the red-stained snow. The bleak pale sun that glittered so blindingly from the ice-fields and the snow-covered plains struck sheens of silver from rent corselet and broken blade, where the dead lay as they had fallen. The nerveless hand yet gripped the broken hilt; helmeted heads back-drawn in the death-throes, tilted red beards and golden beards grimly upward, as if in last invocation to Ymir the frost-giant, god of a warrior-race...</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nIt is said that the battlefield is truly Ymir\'s altar. The war god does not want murdered sacrifices so much as beautiful deaths during the din of glorious combat. Yet those most devoted to the Lord of Storm and War still find themselves constructing places where they can directly commune with their god through the medium of spilt blood. On the cold winds of deadly winter, one might hear the grinding whisper of the Father of Giants saying, \'You get what you give.\'")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80975_ShortDesc", "A statue in the image of Mitra that pours forth water")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80975_LongDesc", "Through the mysteries of Mitra it is possible to call water to well forth eternally. This affirmation of Mitra\'s power is marred somewhat by those who claim that the worshippers of Mitra only build these over pre-existing streams.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80976_ShortDesc", "A statue in the image of Mitra that radiates holy light")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80976_LongDesc", "It is said that the lights on these statues will burn eternally as long as Mitra has a single faithful follower. It can be argued, of course, that a single faithful follower of Mitra would also keep the light burning to perpetuate the mysteries of Mitra and therefore create a paradox which has theologians everywhere going to sleep each night with a sore head.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80986_ShortDesc", "A cooked, rare fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80986_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">It takes an Argossean merchant to wring wealth out of a little waterfront shop that stank of rotten fish and cheap wine.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThe bounty of the rivers and seas are a major food source for many peoples in Hyboria. Such fare may be prepared by roasting, boiling, and many other methods besides.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80991_ShortDesc", "A rare fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80991_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is harvested from small fish not known for being good eating. It is not particularly filling or flavorful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80996_ShortDesc", "A dried and stuffed fish mounted on a wooden plack")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80996_LongDesc", "Fishermen often keep their most memorable catch as a trophy. Some are kept for the memories, others to impress, and yet others are kept for the sole reason of having something on the wall. Looking at this piece, you cannot help but wonder what reason could possibly be behind this one.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_83007_ShortDesc", "A furnace for smelting metals and stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_83007_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Logs flamed in the wide fireplace, for there was a frosty edge to the air, and a great meat pasty in a stone platter stood smoking on a broad mahogany board.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nDesigned to heat ore to incredibly high temperatures in order to extract pure metals, furnaces require fuels such as coal or wood and ores for processing and catalysts such as Steelfire for strengthening. Intense heat can also be used to harden certain types of stone and a furnace can be used in conjunction with other concoctions to create hardened stone bricks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88887_ShortDesc", "A skull impaled on a stake")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88887_LongDesc", "There is something disconcerting about the grinning skull attached to this stake. Though the eye sockets are hollow and the skin and flesh have been long since scoured from the bones, it still appears to be watchful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88890_ShortDesc", "This is a skull taken from a dead enemy")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88890_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the dead rise to fight once again. Perhaps they rise due to the long forgotten command of a necromancer. Perhaps they rise to the singing of a song that the living cannot hear. \nWhatever wakes them, they must still be put to sleep once more.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88891_ShortDesc", "The shell from a Shaleback Hatchling")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88891_LongDesc", "This shell, taken from a Shaleback Hatchling, is brittle and easily chipped. It cannot be used to make weapons or armor nor is it useful for potions or food. Essentially a baby Shaleback was killed for no reason. Way to go.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88892_ShortDesc", "A warning sign as good as any.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88892_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the dead rise to fight once again. Perhaps they rise due to the long forgotten command of a necromancer. Perhaps they rise to the singing of a song that the living cannot hear. \nWhatever wakes them, they must still be put to sleep once more.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88897_LongDesc", "Shaped of clay and fired in a kiln, jugs are used to store liquids and perishable foodstuff.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88899_ShortDesc", "A placeable divider for the easily embarrased")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88899_LongDesc", "While noone would claim Stygians are easily embarrased, some  visitors to the brothels in Khem may wish for some privacy. While the folding screens do not muffle the screams of what goes on behind them, they do obscure the line of sight.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88900_ShortDesc", "A wooden table of Stygian design")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88900_LongDesc", "Tables vary in shape and size, materials and decoration based on the culture and craftsmanship of their maker.\nThis one is a wooden circle.\nThe artisan was probably hoping to decorate the table with dozens of interesting objects and thereby distract from the lack of imagination in the creation of the table itself.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88901_ShortDesc", "A round wooden table")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88901_LongDesc", "Tables vary in shape and size, materials and decoration based on the culture and craftsmanship of their maker.\nThis one is a wooden circle.\nThe artisan was probably hoping to decorate the table with dozens of interesting objects and thereby distract from the lack of imagination in the creation of the table itself.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88902_ShortDesc", "A rack for displaying weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88902_LongDesc", "Boastful warriors and craftsman alike enjoy adorning their strongholds with the weapons of their conquered foes.\n\nHumbler heroes still find such display racks useful, not least for being able to store weapons in places where they would otherwise seem out of place.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89001_ShortDesc", "A small campfire for cooking and keeping warm")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89001_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Lie here.' He indicated a clean-swept space close to a small flickering fire. He saw no incongruity in a princess lying down on the naked ground beside a campfire, wrapped in a warrior's cloak.</> - Black Colossus

The campfire is an adventurers best friend when the nights turn cold and the darkness presses in all around. Made from simple branches and twigs, the campfire is an excellent source of light and heat.

Campfires can be used to cook meat which is important given the number of parasites that infect the wild animals of the Exiled Lands. Better to eat some burned meat, than be poisoned for days.

With the light of a campfire, however, comes visibility. Wary travelers would do well to hide their fires, lest they be ambushed in the night by men with unsavory intentions.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89010_ShortDesc", "A large bonfire")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89010_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">They camped that night on the northern slopes of those hills, and hook-nosed, fiery-eyed men of the hill tribes came in scores to squat about the fires and repeat news that had come up out of the mysterious desert. </>- Black Colossus\n\nBuilt of large pieces of wood, the bonfire is a blazing beacon in the night. Bonfires give off more light and heat than their lesser relative, the campfire, which can be an advantage if the priority is to remain warm, or a disadvantage if the priority is to remain hidden.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89011_ShortDesc", "A large campfire for cooking and keeping warm")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89011_LongDesc", "The campfire is an adventurers best friend when the nights turn cold and the darkness presses in all around.\nCampfires can be used to cook meat - which is important given the number of parasites that infect the wild animals of the Exiled Lands. Better to eat some burned meat, than be poisoned for days.\nWith the light of a campfire, however, comes visibility.  A fire this large is very difficult to hide.")

Intense heat can also be used to harden certain types of stone and a furnace can be used in conjunction with other concoctions to create hardened stone bricks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89103_ShortDesc", "A cauldron for mixing concoctions")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89103_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">On the ivory throne-seat Tascela lolled. Bronze bowls of incense rolled their spirals about her; the wisps of smoke curled about her naked limbs like caressing fingers.</> - Red Nails

The humble cauldron is conventionally used by chefs to create meals.  However, the versatility of the cauldron means that it is also sought after by alchemists and sorcerers who concoct strange experiments.

Smelting catalysts such as Steelfire, can only be created by an alchemist who knows the particular combination of ingredients.

This particular type of cauldron was first used commonly in Vendhya.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89104_ShortDesc", "A tannery for processing hides into leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89104_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were young men, but hard and sinewy, with a bearing that comes only to men rendered desperate by adversity. They were clad in mail shirts and worn leather; swords hung at their girdles.</> - A Witch Shall be Born

The stench of the tannery is easily identifiable in the major cities of the world and tanners are often relegated to the outskirts of cities or villages, preferably downstream. 

Bark is the most common form of tannin used to convert hide into leather. During the process it breaks down into Tar, which is a useful catalyst for alchemists.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89201_ShortDesc", "A bench covered in tools for crafting armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89201_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">With the firelight glinting from his blue steel armor, he seemed like an image of steel - dynamic power for the moment quiescent; not resting, but motionless for the instant, awaiting the signal to plunge again into terrific action.</> - Black Colossus\n\nCreating armor, particularly metal armor, requires a large number of exotic tools. This armormaking bench can be used to create anything from the lightest leather armor to hardened steel armor. Provided that the raw materials are available, of course.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89301_ShortDesc", "A bench covered in tools for shaping metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89301_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">That is to say, they had learned to work crudely in copper and tin, which were found scantily in their country, and for which latter metal they raided into the mountains of Zingara, or traded hides, whale's teeth, walrus tusks and such few things as savages have to trade.</>- The Hyborian Age

Smithing is a well-known and oft-used profession in the Hyborian kingdoms. In the larger cities and towns, smiths are forced to join guilds that offer them a certain amount of political protection, while enforcing a rigorous set of standards of work and tools.

This bench contains many of the tools that smiths need, but in the Exiled Lands, there are no standards to be enforced.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89302_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">That is to say, they had learned to work crudely in copper and tin, which were found scantily in their country, and for which latter metal they raided into the mountains of Zingara, or traded hides, whale's teeth, walrus tusks and such few things as savages have to trade.</>- The Hyborian Age

This bench contains many of the tools that smiths need, but in the Exiled Lands, there are no standards to be enforced.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89401_ShortDesc", "A bench covered in tools for carpentry")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89401_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Our merciful sovereign offers you one more chance, Countess,\" said the tallest of the three, and he spoke Aquilonian without an accent. \"He bids me say that if you soften your proud, rebellious spirit, he will still open his arms to you. If not-\' he gestured toward a grim wooden block in the center of the cell. It was blackly stained, and showed many deep nicks as if a keen edge, cutting through some yielding substance, had sunk into the wood.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThe ability to work wood is a useful skill for anybody interested in creating buildings and furniture. This bench is covered with all of the implements that one needs to create anything from houses to chairs.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89402_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Our merciful sovereign offers you one more chance, Countess,\" said the tallest of the three, and he spoke Aquilonian without an accent. \"He bids me say that if you soften your proud, rebellious spirit, he will still open his arms to you. If not-\' he gestured toward a grim wooden block in the center of the cell. It was blackly stained, and showed many deep nicks as if a keen edge, cutting through some yielding substance, had sunk into the wood.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThe ability to work wood is a useful skill for anybody interested in creating buildings and furniture. This bench is covered with all of the implements that one needs to create anything from houses to chairs.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89801_ShortDesc", "A foundation for building siege equipment")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89801_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He had sent his light riders, his spahis, inland to ravage the country, and had reared up his siege engines in the plain.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This foundation is designed to be a reinforced base for building siege engines that require stability as they are fired.

Siege engines require immense amounts of labor to craft and maintain. They are expensive to transport, and the working parts break often, requiring constant supervision.

It is undoubted, however, that beneath the gods themselves, they are one of the most powerful weapons available to any army.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89811_ShortDesc", "A rotating base for a trebuchet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89811_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">On the landward side mangonels rained boulders and tree-trunks among the defenders, shattering through roofs and crushing humans like beetles; rams pounded incessantly at the stones; sappers burrowed like moles in the earth, sinking their mines beneath the towers.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This base piece of the trebuchet, once placed on a siege foundation, can be upgraded with a  frame to reach full functionality.

In the so-called civilized kingdoms of Hyboria, nobles build great palaces with walls of mighty stone to protect themselves from their enemies at court and abroad. 

The solution to sturdy walls and cowardly nobility is the steadfast trebuchet. A machine of immense power, the trebuchet can be used to fling stones, corpses and even specially designed explosives.

Their weakness is their immobility, they cannot be easily moved once placed and finding the correct range and angle requires time and patience. With repeated use, it is almost certain that some or all of the pieces of the trebuchet will degrade and need to be replaced.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89813_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'No man living could throw that rock across this glade. It's a task for siege engines. Yet here there are no mangonels or ballistas.'</> - Shadows in the Moonlight

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89852_ShortDesc", "Ammunition for the trebuchet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89852_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They pushed on grimly, over soil charred and blackened, where the naked rock had in places been turned to lava by the explosion of those diabolical bombs.</> - People of the Black Circle

Using similar ingredients to those found in Kothic Demon-fire, this explosive barrage is designed to melt the very stones that it explodes upon, slowly burning all caught in its wrath.

It is expensive to create, however, and those who use it in battle earn a reputation for ruthlessness and unusual cruelty.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89911_ShortDesc", "A wheel that strengthens the body as it breaks the mind")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89911_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He did not care anymore. Life and death... the same.</> - Conan the Barbarian \n\nThis wheel is based on a design that originally comes from the mountains and valleys of Vanaheim. It is unclear whether it serves any purpose other than to keep prisoners passive and exhausted until they can be used for more productive tasks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90000_ShortDesc", "A map showing the ancient kingdom of the Giant-kings")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90000_LongDesc", "This room is a copy of the maproom that exists beneath the Unnamed City. In times past, the Giant-kings used sorcery to quickly move their slaves around their kingdom, attuning their bracelets to different areas and then using the map room to get there.

While the terrain is slightly different, owing to the eons that have passed since the creation of the original map, this map room still retains the ability to quickly send anybody with a bracelet to one of the attuned obelisks.

It is speculated that in the dim past, the obelisks served as a form of permission for slaves - the more trusted the slave, the more access to obelisks. Now, it is simply a matter of finding them, wherever they are.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90001_ShortDesc", "A square foundation piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90001_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting sandstone buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90002_ShortDesc", "A square wall piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90002_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90003_ShortDesc", "A square ceiling piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90003_LongDesc", "It is said that nobody is truly home until they have a roof over their head. Across the civilizations of Hyboria, rooves are made from a diverse number of materials from clay-fired tiles warmed in the kilns of Agarapar to the roughly thatched rooves of the Nordheimers. 
In the Exiled Lands, however, materials are limited. Something to keep the sandstorms at bay and the bat demons from swooping down and snatching people while they sleep is probably good enough.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90004_ShortDesc", "A doorframe made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90004_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.
A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.
The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90005_ShortDesc", "Stairs of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90005_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90006_ShortDesc", "A wedge shaped piece of sandstone ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90006_LongDesc", "Wedge shaped building pieces allow greater flexibility in the shapes available to builders.\nCobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.\nDespite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90007_ShortDesc", "A sandstone wall with space for a window")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90007_LongDesc", "Windows provide great vantage points for archers without forcing them to leave the safety of stout walls.\nCobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.\nDespite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90008_ShortDesc", "A simple wooden door")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90008_LongDesc", "Created from the most basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this simple wooden door offers access to friends and denies it to foes.\nThe wood has aged in the desert sun and will not be strong enough to hold out determined foes, but it will keep the weather outside.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90009_ShortDesc", "A pillar made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90009_LongDesc", "Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Pillars offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90010_ShortDesc", "A fence piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90010_LongDesc", "Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
This low fence is not designed to keep enemies out, but rather to provide defensive archers with a measure of cover between shots. 
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90011_ShortDesc", "A triangle foundation made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90011_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting sandstone buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90013_ShortDesc", "A sloped roof piece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90013_LongDesc", "Cobbled together from plant fiber and flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Sloped rooves are practical for channeling debris from the roof.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90020_ShortDesc", "A foundation for placing walls and fences")
column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90024_ShortDesc", "A sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90024_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90069_ShortDesc", "Stairs of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90069_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90070_ShortDesc", "Stairs made of Stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90070_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built - if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90101_ShortDesc", "A square-shaped Stonebrick foundation")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90101_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90102_ShortDesc", "A wall of Stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90102_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90103_ShortDesc", "A ceiling piece of Stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90103_LongDesc", "It is said that nobody is truly home until they have a roof over their head. Across the civilizations of Hyboria, rooves are made from a diverse number of materials - from clay-fired tiles warmed in the kilns of Agarapar to the roughly thatched rooves of the Nordheimers. 
In the Exiled Lands, however, materials are limited. Something to keep the sandstorms at bay and the bat demons from swooping down and snatching people while they sleep is probably good enough.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90104_ShortDesc", "A doorframe of Stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90104_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.
A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.
The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90106_ShortDesc", "A wedge shaped piece of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90106_LongDesc", "Wedges are used to expand the possibilities of a building.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90107_ShortDesc", "A frame made of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90107_LongDesc", "This is a wall with some stones removed to create space for a window. Useful for letting in natural light and keeping an eye on the surroundings.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90108_ShortDesc", "A door of reinforced wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90108_LongDesc", "Shaped wooden planks reinforced with iron bands are used to create this solid door. While providing access, this door also provides significant protection against intruders.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90109_ShortDesc", "A pillar made of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90109_LongDesc", "Pillars offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90110_ShortDesc", "A low fence of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90110_LongDesc", "This low fence is not designed to keep enemies out, but rather to provide defensive archers with a measure of cover between shots. \nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90111_ShortDesc", "A wedged shaped Stonebrick foundation")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90111_LongDesc", "Wedge foundations allow unique shapes to be created when building.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90113_ShortDesc", "A sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90113_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90114_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90115_LongDesc", "These walls are useful for filling out gaps left by odd building pieces.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90120_ShortDesc", "A fence foundation of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90120_LongDesc", "Fence foundations can be placed in locations where fences and walls are needed, but the larger foundations of a building do not need to be placed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90121_ShortDesc", "Framework for a large gate")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90121_LongDesc", "The best battle, as they say, is the one you never have to fight. With formidable enough gates, the enemies will think twice about attacking any fortress. Not simply because the scale of the gates has them concerned about getting inside, but because large gates imply large inhabitants and armies get nervous when they think they might be outnumbered.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90122_ShortDesc", "Sturdy doors to keep enemies at bay")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90122_LongDesc", "These large doors are designed to allow access for large groups of people in and out of safe areas. Raiders and bandits make walls a must have in the Exiled Lands and the protection afforded by gates such as these should not be taken for granted.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90208_ShortDesc", "A heavy door, reinforced with metal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90208_LongDesc", "One of the strongest doors that can be crafted, the heavy door offers protection against everything but the most powerful of enemy tricks.\nRaging hordes have been kept at bay by such doors and with a simple locking mechanism they become proof against incursions into structures.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90223_ShortDesc", "Crenelated walls for placing siege cauldrons and archers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90223_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Under the walls the mailed figures swarmed, battering at the gates, rearing up scaling-ladders, pushing storming-towers, thronged with spearmen, against the turrets.'</> - The Scarlet Citadel

The strength of walls during a siege is determined by two things - the strength of building itself and the ability of defenders to cleanly shoot enemies that are attacking.

These crenelated walls are a common design, effective at giving archers a clear space for firing on enemies as well as providing a niche for placing siege cauldrons and other defensive mechanisms.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90224_ShortDesc", "A mechanism that allows or denies access to a gate")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90224_LongDesc", "Connected to a gate, the drawbridge is designed as a defensive measure, denying approaching enemies easy access to the gate. The drawbridge is operated by a lever.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90225_ShortDesc", "A mechanism that allows vertical travel without climbing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90225_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Then, looping the loose end of his silk rope about Natala's hips, and cautioning her to hold on with both hands, he lifted her through the window and lowered her the thirty-odd feet to the earth.'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

The mechanics of creating such a machine - involving counter-weights, pulleys and other fine details - are considered sorcery by the ignorant and wisdom by the enlightened.

The practical benefits of such a machine cannot be denied, but civilized peoples who grow too reliant upon them will find that a climbing horde of barbarians can be just as effective, and infinitely more deadly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90226_ShortDesc", "A mechanism that allows horizontal travel")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90226_LongDesc", "The mechanics of creating such a machine - involving counter-weights, pulleys and other fine details - are considered sorcery by the ignorant and wisdom by the enlightened.\n\nThe practical benefits of such a machine cannot be denied, but civilized peoples who grow too reliant upon them will find that a horde of barbarians following a rope hand over hand can be just as effective, and infinitely more deadly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90227_ShortDesc", "A cauldron attached to a simple lever")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90227_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Take your plots to hell with you!' he roared, and like a sack of salt, he hurled the prince of Pellia far out, to fall through empty space for a hundred and fifty feet. The people gave back as the body came hurtling down, to smash on the marble pave, spattering blood and brains, and lie crushed in its splintered armor, like a mangled beetle.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Crafting fortifications is the beginning of a coherent siege strategy but it is the least interesting and least creative part of the equation. A good fortification includes structures that are built for a specific purpose - such as murder holes created to lure enemies through a gauntlet of deadly traps.

These siege cauldrons, filled with boiling tar, are simply another tool in the arsenal of a siege engineer. They can be used to discourage eager climbers or to wreak havoc on enemies trapped in a murder hole.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90229_ShortDesc", "A heavy door, reinforced with metal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90229_LongDesc", "One of the strongest doors that can be crafted, the heavy door offers protection against everything but the most powerful of enemy tricks.\nRaging hordes have been kept at bay by such doors and with a simple locking mechanism they become proof against incursions into structures.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90243_ShortDesc", "A square-shaped Insulated Wood foundation")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90243_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Built of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90244_ShortDesc", "A wall of Insulated Wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90244_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Built of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90245_ShortDesc", "A ceiling piece of Insulated Wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90245_LongDesc", "It is said that nobody is truly home until they have a roof over their head. Across the civilizations of Hyboria, rooves are made from a diverse number of materials - from clay-fired tiles warmed in the kilns of Agarapar to the roughly thatched rooves of the Nordheimers. 
In the Exiled Lands, however, materials are limited. Something to keep the blizzards at bay and the bat demons from swooping down and snatching people while they sleep is probably good enough.
Built of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90246_ShortDesc", "A doorframe of Insulated Wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90246_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.
A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.
The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.
Built of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90247_ShortDesc", "Stairs made of Insulated Wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90247_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built - if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Built of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90248_ShortDesc", "A wedge shaped piece of Insulated Wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90248_LongDesc", "Wedges are used to expand the possibilities of a building.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90249_ShortDesc", "A frame made of Insulated Wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90249_LongDesc", "This is a wall with some stones removed to create space for a window. Useful for letting in natural light and keeping an eye on the surroundings.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90250_ShortDesc", "A door of reinforced wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90250_LongDesc", "Shaped wooden planks reinforced with iron bands are used to create this solid door. While providing access, this door also provides significant protection against intruders.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90251_ShortDesc", "A pillar made of Insulated Wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90251_LongDesc", "Pillars offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90252_ShortDesc", "A low fence of Insulated Wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90252_LongDesc", "This low fence is not designed to keep enemies out, but rather to provide defensive archers with a measure of cover between shots. \nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90253_LongDesc", "Wedge foundations allow unique shapes to be created when building.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90254_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in blizzards as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90260_LongDesc", "Fence foundations can be placed in locations where fences and walls are needed, but the larger foundations of a building do not need to be placed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90261_ShortDesc", "Framework for a large gate")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90261_LongDesc", "The best battle, as they say, is the one you never have to fight. With formidable enough gates, the enemies will think twice about attacking any fortress. Not simply because the scale of the gates has them concerned about getting inside, but because large gates imply large inhabitants and armies get nervous when they think they might be outnumbered.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90262_ShortDesc", "Sturdy doors to keep enemies at bay")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90262_LongDesc", "These large doors are designed to allow access for large groups of people in and out of safe areas. Raiders and bandits make walls a must have in the Exiled Lands and the protection afforded by gates such as these should not be taken for granted.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90263_ShortDesc", "A square foundation piece made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90263_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Black Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90283_ShortDesc", "Crenelated walls for placing siege cauldrons and archers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90283_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Under the walls the mailed figures swarmed, battering at the gates, rearing up scaling-ladders, pushing storming-towers, thronged with spearmen, against the turrets.'</> - The Scarlet Citadel

The strength of walls during a siege is determined by two things - the strength of building itself and the ability of defenders to cleanly shoot enemies that are attacking.

These crenelated walls are a common design, effective at giving archers a clear space for firing on enemies as well as providing a niche for placing siege cauldrons and other defensive mechanisms.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90284_ShortDesc", "A hatch frame made of sandstone")
column4:

A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.

The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90294_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90295_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90295_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90296_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90296_LongDesc", "These walls are useful for filling out gaps left by odd building pieces.\nReinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90306_LongDesc", "When moving huge wheeled wagons filled to the brim with rare resources, luxury goods or even slaves, ramps are much preferred over stairs, for self-evident reasons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90323_ShortDesc", "A square-shaped Insulated Wood foundation")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90323_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Built of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92099_ShortDesc", "Arrows made from the hollowed bones of a winged demon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92099_LongDesc", "These arrows were not crafted as much as ripped from the dead bodies of the winged Children of Jhil.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92119_ShortDesc", "A still beating heart")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92119_LongDesc", "The heart, still beating, was taken from the chest of a nordheimer hero. A worthy sacrifice to Ymir.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92127_ShortDesc", "A coating that harms the undead")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92127_LongDesc", "Cimmerians fear not creatures of flesh and blood but those of an undead nature cannot be killed by normal means. Forced to adapt people of the Forgotten Tribe found a way to make the rotting flesh sear by coating their weapons with this salve.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92133_ShortDesc", "A fragment of a stone tablet with runes carved on it")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92133_LongDesc", "The genious of Thorgar was rumored to be unrivalled in the days of old. His descendants inherited tablets with recipes carved in ancient runes supposedly only legible to his closest kin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92134_ShortDesc", "An aged manuscript")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92134_LongDesc", "Contrary to a common belief, the teachings of a frost giant did not teach Thorgar smithing skills. In actuality, his skills were honed by countless experimentations with ice and steel. Some of his findings are noted down in this parchment. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92135_ShortDesc", "An ancient crest")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92135_LongDesc", "A symbol of acknowledgement and status among Aesir craftsmen. Thorgar received it from King Dunkar as a reward for his contributions to the tribe.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92141_ShortDesc", "A scroll describing the process for making Aesir armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92141_LongDesc", "This scroll contains the knowledge of a long lost method of crafting the Pride of Aesir armor set capable of withstanding most cruel elements of the North.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92142_ShortDesc", "A spiced dish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92142_LongDesc", "A dish made from the innards of Shoebills, fried with honey, spices and short fibrous strains from nearby plants. This dish will grant protection against cold climates. It also burns your tongue - ever so slightly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92145_ShortDesc", "Aclohol. Alloco? Alocolol? it\'s booze.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92145_LongDesc", "This will get you good and drunk and make you speak like a pirate.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92147_ShortDesc", "This dust corrupts but grants night-vision")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92147_LongDesc", "The process of making Argossean Dream Dust is a secret kept by the Black Hand that they do not share willingly. Not that many would be interested in it anyway, given the side-effects. One cannot deny it\'s usefulness though.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92148_ShortDesc", "A scroll describing the process for making Aesir armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92148_LongDesc", "This scroll contains the knowledge of a long lost method of crafting the Pride of Aesir armor set capable of withstanding most cruel elements of the North.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92159_ShortDesc", "A pearl")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92159_LongDesc", "Hard. Glistening. Produced by a mollusk. All that you could possibly want.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92168_ShortDesc", "Strands of black fiber")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92168_LongDesc", "These strands of black fiber comes from a plant not commonly found in the Exiled Lands. Where the pirates of the Black Cove has gotten it from is a mystery.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92169_ShortDesc", "Spiced tea")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92169_LongDesc", "This tea has an immediate warming effect on whomever imbibes it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92170_ShortDesc", "A spiced dish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92170_LongDesc", "This dish has an immediate warming effect on whomever eats it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92171_ShortDesc", "A spiced dish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92171_LongDesc", "This dish has an immediate warming effect on whomever eats it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92172_ShortDesc", "A spiced dish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92172_LongDesc", "This dish has an immediate warming effect on whomever eats it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92173_ShortDesc", "A spiced dish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92173_LongDesc", "This dish has an immediate warming effect on whomever eats it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92174_ShortDesc", "A rare luxury item in the Exiled Lands")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92174_LongDesc", "While normal spice is relatively easy to obtain, the more zesty and tasty spices are still a luxury commodity.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92175_ShortDesc", "Reading this scroll will grand you knowledge")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92175_LongDesc", "Reading this scroll will teach you how to craft the Vehemence Elixir.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92178_ShortDesc", "A weapon oil that increases weapon damage temporarily")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92178_LongDesc", "Prepared by a secret process, known only to those slaves of the Giant-kings who toiled in the arena, oils such as these were used to subtly influence the outcomes of arena combat.\nThis oil, when coating a weapon, causes additional pain with every blow, until the coating has worn off.\nThe downside is that the oil is acidic and eats away at the weapon over time, rendering it brittle and much more likely to break.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92179_ShortDesc", "A weapon oil that increases the armor penetration of a weapon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92179_LongDesc", "Prepared by a secret process, known only to those slaves of the Giant-kings who toiled in the arena, oils such as these were used to subtly influence the outcomes of arena combat.\nThis oil, when coating a weapon, causes the weapon to slide toward weak points in the armor, allowing it to more easily penetrate the surface.\nThe downside is that the oil is acidic and eats away at the weapon over time, rendering it brittle and much more likely to break.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92180_ShortDesc", "A weapon oil that decreases the stamina cost of a weapon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92180_LongDesc", "Prepared by a secret process, known only to those slaves of the Giant-kings who toiled in the arena, oils such as these were used to subtly influence the outcomes of arena combat.\nThis oil, when coating a weapon, seems to ease the passage of the weapon through the air. Blades cut more easily, and maces seem to leap forward of their own volition.\nThe downside is that the oil is acidic and eats away at the weapon over time, rendering it brittle and much more likely to break.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92181_ShortDesc", "A weapon oil that increases the concussion damage of a weapon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92181_LongDesc", "Prepared by a secret process, known only to those slaves of the Giant-kings who toiled in the arena, oils such as these were used to subtly influence the outcomes of arena combat.\nThis oil, when coating a weapon, gives off a powerful, sweet odor that makes those who smell it feel lethargic. When used in battle, it is not certain whether the wounds inflicted, or just the odor are responsible for the additional concussive effect.\nThe downside is that the oil is acidic and eats away at the weapon over time, rendering it brittle and much more likely to break.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92182_ShortDesc", "A tool oil that enhances the effectiveness of harvesting")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92182_LongDesc", "Prepared by a secret process, known only to those slaves of the Giant-kings who toiled in the arena, oils such as these were used to subtly influence the outcomes of arena combat.\nThis oil was discarded when it appeared to have no significant use in combat, stacked in leaky barrels in a corner of the arena. Later, it was observed that the oil, when in contact with organic matter, seemed to expand and mimic the characteristics of simple inorganic and organic structures. The arena slaves began using on the tools while harvesting meat from the corpses of the fallen, and it created an abundance unheard of in the arena before.\nThe downside is that the oil is acidic and eats away at the weapon over time, rendering it brittle and much more likely to break.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92186_ShortDesc", "A set of armor joints made for maneuverability")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92186_LongDesc", "These armor joints will allow an increased range of movement when climbing.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92187_ShortDesc", "A set of reinforcing plates that can attached to increase the strength of armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92187_LongDesc", "Designed to protect in battle, it can be disastrous if armor shatters beneath a powerful blow. Wise warriors seek to shore up their weaknesses, often by reinforcing the weaker joints of their armor.\n\nAttaching these thick plates to any set of clothing will increase its armor value considerably.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92188_ShortDesc", "A set of tools that increase both damage and armor penetration")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92188_LongDesc", "This set of tools contain various implements to enhance the damage as well as armor penetration of a weapon. Modifying a weapon in this fashion will greatly reduce the durability of the weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92189_ShortDesc", "A fitting for a weapon that allows for greater handling")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92189_LongDesc", "This weapon fitting increases the damage for quick and light attacks but does so by removing some of the weight behind the blows, reducing heavy damage as a trade-off.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92190_ShortDesc", "A reinforcement that can be used to make weapons and armor more durable")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92190_LongDesc", "A warrior relies on their strength, their skill and their weapon to carry them in battle. If any of these are broken in the clash of swords, it puts life and limb at risk.

This reinforcement can be used to find the flaws in a weapon or piece of armor and buttress them against the storm of battle.

This advanced reinforcement will increase the durability of a weapon or a piece of armor slightly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92191_ShortDesc", "A set of bulky armor plates to fit inside armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92191_LongDesc", "These armor plates fit snugly in or over armor pieces but increases the weight of such armors greatly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92192_ShortDesc", "A treatise explaining the usage of various weapon oils")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92192_LongDesc", "Spoken in a wavering, ancient voice, this memory note contains the ramblings of an ancient Giant-king on the various oils developed and used by the slaves of the arena.\nThough the Priestking gave him strict instructions never to reveal the nature of oils to others, the arena master took it upon himself to record the knowledge, in case it might be of use to others of his kind in the future.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_899195_ShortDesc", "A potion that incites rage and strength")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_899195_LongDesc", "Drinking this potion will make the imbiber fly into a berserk frenzy, increasing damage and armor but  prevent healing. Once the effects of the potion wears off, the imbiber becomes fatigued.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_899196_ShortDesc", "Ancient desert elixir, drinking causes shivering under the hottest sun and burn the skin on cold winter nights.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_899196_LongDesc", "Created by mad sorcerers of Stygia this elixir allowed their armies to withstand the cruelest of hazards and would have paved a way to conquest of the northern lands was it not for the Aquilonian armies stopping them during the battle of Styx. All the trails revealing a true nature of magical concoctions ended there and recipe was never found.")
